! Changelog

|!Version |!Date |!Changes |
|0.0.87 |2026-05-29 |''New setting: "Pin all pill rows" ‚Äî render every pill strip (Visibility, Reach, Search-in, Filter) even when no pills are pushed.'' Discoverability / dev aid. Default off; toggle live via Settings ‚Üí Pin all pill rows (or set `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/pin-pill-rows` to `yes`). When on, the popup picks up `rcp-pin-pill-rows` and a single CSS rule forces every strip's `display: flex`. The strips were already always in the DOM (so focus mechanics work cleanly during transitions); this just unhides the empty container. Lets a user see WHERE each strip sits and what its accent colour is before pushing pills into it ‚Äî useful when teaching the palette or while authoring new pill tiddlers. Wired exactly like `details-always-on`: new constant `PIN_PILL_ROWS_CONFIG` in `cp-constants.js`, new config tiddler shipping default `no`, new settings row (toggle, order 45), `isPinPillRows()` reader + `_updatePinPillRows()` class-toggler on the widget prototype, change-hook listener in the existing `_wikiChangeHook` so live config edits flip the strips without reopening the palette. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-constants.js`, new `config/pin-pill-rows.tid`, new `settings/pin-pill-rows.tid`, `widgets/cascade-palette-widget.js` (initial call after `popupEl` creation + change-hook branch + the two methods), `styles.tid` (4-selector rule keyed off `.rcp-pin-pill-rows`), `settings.tid` (doc entry under //Behaviour//), `doc/reference.tid` (config table row). JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.86 |2026-05-29 |''Filter pills are now global across every view, with virtual menu entries exempted by default ‚Äî matches the contract of the Visibility subsystem.'' Three logical concerns bundled in one bump: global filter-pill semantics + entries exemption (the headline), `renderConstraintHelp` extraction (DRY help-pane rendering), and keyboard cleanup (drop Shift-Enter back-compat alias). The user's intent ("Like Visibility today ‚Äî globally affecting all views") was already true for visibility (predicates run on every row producer) but only partially true for filters: the `_composeFilterSuffix()` string was hand-spliced into the layer's roots/children filter in `cp-views.js` and `cp-actions.js`, but the axis-evaluation path in `cp-axes.js` (`evaluateAxisChainAtDepth`, `sourceAfterAxes`) read `layer.roots` raw ‚Äî so typing `/` in ''By date'' silently did nothing. The Entries view had the opposite problem: filter pills DID apply via the standard layer path, but `+[!is[system]search:title,text<arg>]` killed every entry because plugin-shipped menu entries are system tiddlers. ''(1) New `_applyFilterSuffix(baseFilter, vars, source)` helper in `cp-filters.js`.'' Centralises the contract: callers pass the base filter and get back the narrowed result with virtual entries exempted. No filters active ‚Üí single `_filterInScope` call (zero overhead). Filters active ‚Üí two filterTiddlers calls ‚Äî `base + suffix` for the narrowed real-tiddler set AND `base ‚à© [tag[ENTRY_TAG]]` for entries that were in the broad source ‚Äî unioned with dedup (narrowed-order first, entries-only suffix appended in order). Authors who want a pill to AFFECT entries can still write the expression positively against the entry tag, but the convention is: pill = narrow real tiddlers, input query = narrow whatever's currently rendered. ''(2) `cp-views.js` `_evaluateLayer` switches from suffix concat to the helper.'' The normal layer producer (the most common path ‚Äî Entries view, By namespace, By parent, All tiddlers, Hybrid layers) now uniformly exempts entries. ''(3) `cp-axes.js` `evaluateAxisChainAtDepth` + `sourceAfterAxes` route through the helper.'' "By date" and any custom axis-bucketed view finally see the active filter pills. Empty post-filter buckets vanish from the row list naturally ‚Äî bucket existence IS the "drillable" signal (replaces the count-driven cue, which still works but is now redundant). Bucket counts (`g.items.length`) remain populated since they come for free from the `groupBy` reducer over the already-narrowed source; the badge shows the correct post-filter count when the view opted in via `ca-view-show-count`. ''(4) `_isLeafInLayer` + `_childCountForLayer` (cp-views.js) become filter-aware.'' Leaf detection on tree containers now uses the suffix-narrowed children ‚Äî a tiddler whose children all fail the active filter renders as a leaf (no chevron). The expensive per-row enumeration in `_childCountForLayer` is gated to `view.showCount && !filters.length` so adding a filter pill to a large tree view doesn't pay O(rows √ó children) on every render; the chevron alone tells the user "drillable" when filters are active. ''(5) `cp-actions.js` `evaluateFilterStage` routes through the helper too.'' Dynamic filter stages (entered via `ca-next-scope` from a leaf row, action-menu rows, etc.) inherit the same entries-exemption contract. ''(6) `_evaluateEntriesLayer` unchanged.'' The synthetic entries layer never went through the suffix ‚Äî it stays unfiltered by design, matching the user's "virtual menu entries always present" rule. ''(7) Docs.'' `doc/reference.tid` `ca-filter-expr` row gains the new "applied globally across all views; virtual entries exempted by default" wording. `ca-view-show-count` row notes the "suppressed while a filter pill is active for tree containers; axis buckets keep their count" behaviour. `cp-visibility.js` header block updated ‚Äî the old "ONLY affects root-entry rows" claim was a leftover; visibility has been row-universal since the entries-layer refactor, and the new wording reflects that. ''(8) `renderConstraintHelp` extraction (cp-pillstrip.js).'' Six pill-strip help-pane renderers ‚Äî filter / visibility / reach / field / leader / preset ‚Äî each contained the same ~20-line DOM-building boilerplate (`while (firstChild) removeChild` + title `<div>` + help `<div>` + `<dl>` of fields + `rcp-showing-detail` popup class toggle). Hoisted into `pillstrip.renderConstraintHelp(widget, {title, help, rows})`. Each caller's `_maybeRender*Help` shrinks to a rows-array build + a delegate call. Same DOM output; specs unaffected. ''(9) Drop Shift-Enter back-compat alias (cp-keyboard.js).'' `fireSelected(e.ctrlKey || e.shiftKey)` had carried the Shift-Enter alias for Ctrl-Enter ("keep palette open after firing") since the 0.2-era; the deprecation note said "remove in v0.3". 0.0.86 removes it: only Ctrl-Enter keeps the palette open now. Shift-Enter is free for any future binding. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-filters.js` (new helper + ENTRY_TAG import + delegated help renderer), `widgets/cp-views.js` (`_evaluateLayer`, `_isLeafInLayer`, `_childCountForLayer`, count-gate on tree-container build), `widgets/cp-axes.js` (`evaluateAxisChainAtDepth`, `sourceAfterAxes`), `widgets/cp-actions.js` (`evaluateFilterStage`), `widgets/cp-visibility.js` (header comment + delegated help renderer), `widgets/cp-pillstrip.js` (new `renderConstraintHelp` export), `widgets/cp-leaders.js`, `widgets/cp-reach-pills.js`, `widgets/cp-field-pills.js`, `widgets/cp-preset-pills.js` (all delegate to `renderConstraintHelp`), `widgets/cp-keyboard.js` (drop Shift-Enter alias), `widgets/cascade-palette-widget.js` (this.filters comment), `doc/reference.tid` (two table rows), `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. All 192 cascade-palette Jasmine specs + 52 gotcha fixtures pass byte-stably. JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.85 |2026-05-29 |''Phase E ‚Äî DOM/logic separation + Playwright e2e infrastructure.'' Two narrow pure-function extractions (highlight match computation + keyboard dispatch table) gain isolated test coverage; one latent runtime bug fixed; Playwright e2e infrastructure landed for the palette with 5 specs proving the open/close cycle + narrowing. 192 cascade-palette Jasmine specs (up from 151), 1953 total / 0 failures. ''(1) `_highlightMatches(item, query, fieldOverride, globalDefault)` ‚Äî extracted from filterByQuery (cp-actions.js).'' Pre-Phase-E the per-item match-computation was inline inside the result-narrowing loop; carving it out makes it (a) testable in isolation, (b) reusable by ad-hoc renderers (e.g. a diagnostics view that wants to highlight a query against arbitrary cascade items without going through narrowing). Pure ‚Äî no mutation of `item`; that's filterByQuery's job. Optional injection of resolved-field-list params so hot loops resolve once and share. Backward-compatible: `filterByQuery` now delegates per-item, keeping its narrow-and-stamp behaviour byte-identical (proven by existing specs). ''(2) Keyboard dispatch table ‚Äî hoisted from switch (cp-keyboard.js).'' Section-level routing (`(focus) ‚Üí handler-method-name`) is now a pure data table at the top of cp-keyboard. Three exports on the patcher function: `resolveSectionHandler(focus)` (returns method name or null), `dispatchTableSnapshot()` (fresh read-only copy), `SECTION_HANDLERS` (source map). The 12-line switch in `handleKeydown` collapses to a table lookup + typeof guard. Adding a new focus section now means adding one row + writing the handler; the drift-detector spec catches mismatch. ''(3) Bug fix ‚Äî dead `preview` switch branch removed.'' The pre-Phase-E switch had `case "preview": this._handleKeydownPreview(e, stage)`, but `_handleKeydownPreview` was never defined ‚Äî any user reaching that branch would crash with TypeError. The drift-detector spec caught this. The new dispatch table omits the preview row entirely; the typeof guard in `handleKeydown` silently no-ops unknown focus values, so preview focus (a native-focusable DOM element handled by the browser) is properly inert. ''(4) New 20-spec `test/test-highlight.js`.'' Coverage: empty/null query ‚Üí []; substring match in single field with case-insensitivity + first-occurrence; len = query length (not matched substring length); multi-field collection; field-list ORDER preserved; field resolution chain (fieldOverride > item.searchFields > globalDefault with all combinations explicitly asserted); no-mutation guarantees; filterByQuery integration (narrow + stamp + clear-stale). ''(5) New 17-spec `test/test-keyboard-dispatch.js`.'' Coverage: 11 known sections ‚Üí expected handler names; unknown focus + falsy + non-string inputs ‚Üí null; prototype-pollution attempts (constructor, __proto__, toString, hasOwnProperty) ‚Üí null; snapshot isolation; per-handler-method existence drift-detector (one spec per section); 11-section exhaustive listing; convention check (`_handleKeydown<Section>`). ''(6) New `tw-tests/tests/e2e/cascade-palette.spec.js` ‚Äî 5 Playwright specs.'' Lands the e2e infrastructure for the palette: mount-point existence; open-message popup activation (backdrop display = flex); typing into input narrows result rows + clearing restores; Escape closes from input focus; open‚Üíclose‚Üíreopen cycle correctness. `rimir/cascade-palette` added to pw-edition's plugins list. Documents the actual DOM contract (no `rcp-open` class ‚Äî visibility is controlled via `.rcp-backdrop` style display, not a class). ''(7) Cumulative test totals.'' 192 cascade-palette Jasmine specs (up from 151 at 0.0.84). Full test edition: 1953 specs / 0 failures. 5 Playwright cascade-palette specs / 0 failures. All 6 cascade-palette gotcha fixtures still byte-identical. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-actions.js` (filterByQuery delegation + new `_highlightMatches` method), `widgets/cp-keyboard.js` (SECTION_HANDLERS table + resolveSectionHandler + dispatchTableSnapshot + bug-fix removal of dead preview branch), new `test/test-highlight.js`, new `test/test-keyboard-dispatch.js`, new `tw-tests/tests/e2e/cascade-palette.spec.js`, `tw-tests/pw-edition/tiddlywiki.info` (cascade-palette added), `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.84 |2026-05-28 |''Phase D ‚Äî schema modernisations with full back-compat.'' Three legacy schemas gain JSON-first alternatives; one tag is renamed; a once-per-session deprecation warning channel makes silent breakage loud. All existing tiddlers keep working unchanged. 151 cascade-palette specs / 1912 total / 0 failures. ''(1) `ca-bind` JSON object alternative (cp-items.js).'' Authors can now write `ca-bind: {"tiddler":"...","field":"...","path":"...","type":"..."}` as a single JSON field instead of four `ca-bind-<key>` fields. New `_resolveBindKey(f, key, default)` helper resolves with JSON-first precedence: parsed-JSON value ‚Üí `ca-bind-<key>` fallback ‚Üí `default`. Mixed schemas allowed: a partial JSON object that omits `path` still reads `ca-bind-path` for it. Invalid JSON falls back to per-field silently (one-time console.warn). Empty JSON values fall through to fallback. Parsed JSON cached on the field map as a non-enumerable `__cpBindParsed` to amortise the 4 lookups per item build. ''(2) `ca-position` JSON array alternative (cp-views.js + cp-position-of.js).'' Authors can write `ca-position: ["A","B"]` (JSON array, detected by leading `[`) instead of `ca-position: A:B` (legacy colon/newline split). Three accepted shapes per slot: JSON array, `"none"` (entry-exclusion sentinel), legacy string. Invalid JSON falls back to legacy parser. Whitespace inside JSON values trimmed; null / blank / empty entries dropped. Both the cp-views position resolver AND the cp-position-of filter operator updated symmetrically. ''(3) Tag rename: `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/field` ‚Üí `.../search-field` (cp-constants.js + cp-field-pills.js).'' The new tag is canonical; the loader reads the UNION of both tags via filter-run concatenation (TW's union semantics dedupe tiddlers tagged with both). Shipped `/field/*.tid` tiddlers (aliases, description, hint, name, search-text, text) migrated to the new tag so the engine doesn't deprecation-warn against its own ships. A once-per-session deprecation warning fires when any USER tiddler still carries the legacy tag, naming the canonical replacement. ''(4) `cp.deprecationWarning(key, message, wiki)` helper (cp-utils.js).'' Module-level state with three exports: `deprecationWarning` (once-per-session warn, always counts), `deprecationCounts()` (read-only snapshot), `resetDeprecationsForTesting()` (spec hook). Gated by config tiddler `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/show-deprecations` (default `yes`); set to anything else to silence console output (counts still accrue). Empty / null / undefined keys ignored. Snapshot returns fresh object so callers can mutate safely. Applied to: `ca-view-source` ‚Üí `ca-view-roots` (warns on author-still-using paths), legacy field tag ‚Üí search-field tag (warns on user-tagged-tiddlers). ''(5) Diagnostics entry `$:/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/diagnostics/deprecations`.'' New `ca-kind: drill` entry surfacing tiddlers still using deprecated schemas ‚Äî `tag[$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/field]` minus search-field-tagged ones, plus `tag[view]has[ca-view-source]`. Authors can drill into the diagnostics view at any time to audit migration progress. ''(6) Three new gotcha fixtures.'' `cp-bind-compat/` exercises 5 settings tiddlers (legacy, full JSON, mixed JSON+legacy, JSON-with-path, invalid-JSON-fallback) and verifies both schemas parse + load via wikitext. `cp-position-json/` exercises 7 entries across JSON array / legacy / mixed / numeric / single / empty-array / invalid-JSON-falls-back-to-legacy paths through `cp-position-of`. `cp-search-field-tag-compat/` verifies union semantics: legacy-only, new-only, both-tagged dedup, and the 6 shipped tiddlers all carry the new tag. ''(7) New 25-spec `test/test-deprecations.js`.'' 10 specs for `deprecationWarning` (once-per-session, key dedup, multi-key, count accrual on dedupe, isolated snapshots, falsy-key guard, show-deprecations gating, missing-config defaults-to-yes, reset hook); 9 specs for `_resolveBindKey` (legacy-only, JSON-overrides, partial-JSON-mixed-fallback, invalid-JSON-fallback, JSON-array-ignored, blank-JSON-falls-through, empty-string-JSON-falls-back, default-when-neither, parsed-JSON-cached); 6 specs for ca-position JSON form (multi-value array, empty-array‚Üíat-root, whitespace-trim, blank-entry-drop, invalid-JSON-falls-back, mixed legacy+JSON-slug); 1 spec for tag-union dedup. Total cascade-palette: 151 specs (up from 126). ''(8) New config tiddler `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/show-deprecations`.'' Defaults to `yes`. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-utils.js` (deprecation helpers), `widgets/cp-items.js` (ca-bind JSON resolver + cache), `widgets/cp-views.js` (JSON array position parser + deprecation warn on ca-view-source), `widgets/cp-position-of.js` (JSON array parsing), `widgets/cp-constants.js` (SEARCH_FIELD_TAG constant), `widgets/cp-field-pills.js` (tag-union loader + deprecation warn), shipped `field/*.tid` retagged, new `config/show-deprecations.tid`, new `diagnostics/deprecations.tid`, new `test/test-deprecations.js`, three new gotcha fixtures, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.83 |2026-05-28 |''Phase C ‚Äî custom filter operators + shared macros.'' Three new `module-type: filteroperator` modules surface the action-catalogue and view-position rules through wikitext, so plugins (kind, orga-palette, etc.) can reuse them for badges / diagnostics without depending on widget internals. ''(1) `widgets/cp-actions-for.js` ‚Äî `[cp-actions-for[<entity-type>]]`.'' Emits action titles whose `ca-entity-type` matches the operand OR is `*` (catalogue + globals branches of `loadActionsForType`). Drafts excluded. Empty / `"*"` / unknown operand surfaces globals only. ''(2) `widgets/cp-actions-applying-to.js` ‚Äî `[cp-actions-applying-to[<title>]]`.'' Iterates `[has[ca-applies]]` actions and evaluates each `ca-applies` filter with `currentTiddler` bound to the operand (mirrors `actionAppliesViaFilter`). Empty operand ‚Üí no results. Uses `options.widget.makeFakeWidgetWithVariables` so nested filter prefixes / `\function` defs resolve correctly ([[tw-gotchas-widget-context#Custom fake widgets...]]). ''(3) `widgets/cp-position-of.js` ‚Äî `[<entry>cp-position-of[<view-slug>]]`.'' Per-input-title source feed; emits effective tree-position parents in the named view. Resolution chain `ca-position-<slug>` ‚Üí `ca-position` ‚Üí `at-root`. Blank slug field falls back to base. `"none"` excludes from that view (emits nothing). Multi-value via colon / newline split. ''(4) `loadActionsForType` switches catalogue path to the operator.'' Previously a single open-coded scan over all action tiddlers; now `[cp-actions-for[<entity>]]` handles catalogue + globals, and the configured-field + `ca-applies` paths remain in JS (they need contextTitle). Union deduplication via a `seen` map; `ca-action-when` narrowing + `readCascadeFields` mapping still applied to the union. Behaviour byte-identical ‚Äî same actions surface, same order. ''(5) New `macros.tid` (`$:/tags/Macro`).'' Author-friendly `\function` wrappers: `cp.label(node)` (caption ‚Üí ca-name ‚Üí title fallback), `cp.actions-applying-to(title)`, `cp.action-applies(entity-type)`, `cp.position-of(view-slug)` (defaults to currentTiddler). Available in every wikitext context via the palette's startup `\import` pragma. ''(6) Three new gotcha fixtures.'' `tw-tests/gotchas/fixtures/cp-actions-for/`, `cp-actions-applying-to/`, `cp-position-of/` lock in operator semantics through byte-stable expected.txt: entity-type matching, draft exclusion, globals-only paths, ca-applies hit/miss combinations, position fallback chain (slug ‚Üí base ‚Üí at-root), `"none"` exclusion at base vs. slug level, blank-slug fall-through, multi-value colon/newline splits, missing-tiddler default. Each loads cascade-palette via `TIDDLYWIKI_PLUGIN_PATH` env override. ''(7) New 26-spec `test/test-filter-ops.js`.'' Per-operator coverage in `new $tw.Wiki()` instances: cp-actions-for catalogue + globals matrix + composability with downstream `has[]`; cp-actions-applying-to filter eval against various ca-applies expressions + skip rules (no-applies / blank-applies / not-tagged); cp-position-of slug-override + base-fallback + at-root default + none-exclusion + blank-slug fall-through + multi-value split (colon and newline). Total cascade-palette specs: 126 (up from 100). Full test edition: 1887 specs / 0 failures. ''(8) Documentation.'' `doc/reference.tid` gains a "Filter operators" table summarising all four operators (`cp-child-of` + the three new ones) ‚Äî operand, source feed, emit semantics. New "Macros" table documents the `\function` wrappers. `doc/examples.tid` ¬ß 16 adds three worked examples: action-count badge composing both action operators, diagnostic listing for an arbitrary tiddler, tree view per-parent query. ''Touches:'' new `widgets/cp-actions-for.js`, `widgets/cp-actions-applying-to.js`, `widgets/cp-position-of.js`, new `macros.tid`, `widgets/cp-stack.js` (loadActionsForType catalogue switch), `doc/reference.tid`, `doc/examples.tid`, new `test/test-filter-ops.js`, three new gotcha fixtures, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.82 |2026-05-28 |''Phase B finished ‚Äî `_filterInScope` helper centralises 22 fake-widget callsites, `buildStageVariables(stage, picked, extras)` formalises the extras-merge contract, and `cp-pillstrip` consolidates 4 pill-strip renderers behind a single `renderPillStripSection` helper. No behaviour change; all 1861 specs pass byte-stably.'' Closes the deferred items from 0.0.81. ''(1) `_filterInScope(filterStr, vars, source)` ‚Äî new method on cp-actions.'' Thin wrapper around `wiki.filterTiddlers(filterStr, makeFakeWidget(vars), source)`. Centralises the [[tw-gotchas-widget-context#Custom fake widgets‚Ä¶]] invariant: every filter-eval that injects variables MUST go through `makeFakeWidget` (which itself delegates to `this.makeFakeWidgetWithVariables` ‚Äî the only way `:filter`/`:map`/`:reduce`/`:sortsub` prefixes spawn per-iteration child widgets correctly). Migrating 22 callsites across cp-actions / cp-leaders / cp-axes / cp-keyboard / cp-side-preview / cp-row-icons / cp-visibility / cp-views / cp-rendering / cp-stack / cp-firing collapses each manual `this.wiki.filterTiddlers(filter, this.makeFakeWidget({...}))` into `this._filterInScope(filter, {...})`. The 3-argument form (axis key/label filters anchored to a single seed title) collapses too: `this._filterInScope(axis.keyFilter, vars, [tiddlerTitle])`. Falsy-vars passthrough preserves the cp-views.js:354 special case where parentTitle is empty (root-level layer eval): null vars ‚Üí null widget ‚Üí TW's wiki.each default source. ''(2) `buildStageVariables(stage, picked, extras)` ‚Äî third parameter.'' Formerly callers manually mutated the returned vars map to inject `payload` / `row-icon-key` / `row-icon-mode` / `keep-open` / etc. (cp-row-icons.js:263-266 and cp-firing.js:503). Now the third argument is a plain extras map merged over the base vars via `Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call` (defensive against prototype pollution). Two callsites cleaned: cp-row-icons.js fire-dispatch and cp-firing.js leaf-action var-build. The method also now tolerates `stage=null` (returns base vars with empty stage-derived fields) ‚Äî replaces the two open-coded fallback objects in cp-row-icons.js:262 and cp-firing.js:460 that previously hand-crafted minimal var maps. ''(3) New `widgets/cp-pillstrip.js` ‚Äî `renderPillStripSection(descriptor)`.'' Single stateless helper for the four symmetric constraint strips: filter, visibility, reach, field. Each was a ~35-line near-duplicate (`while (firstChild) removeChild` + class toggle + foreach pill + per-pill click + √ó button click). Now each cp-{filters,visibility,reach-pills,field-pills}.js's renderer collapses to ~12 lines that build a descriptor (`{widget, stripEl, pills, focusIdx, focusSection, popupHasClass, pillModifier, datasetKey, removeTitle, onSelectAt, onRemoveAt}`) and delegates. Differences between strips become declarative (extra modifier class `rcp-pill-reach`/`rcp-pill-field`, distinct popup class `rcp-has-{filters,visibility,reach,fields}`, distinct dataset key, distinct remove tooltip). Future schema additions (e.g. a `dirty` marker, an icon prefix) land in one place. ''Preset and leader strips are NOT consolidated:'' the preset strip has a trailing `+` save pill, dirty-state marker (active + edited), and scroll-into-view; the leader strip has split key/name child spans. Both retain their standalone implementations. ''(4) New 11-spec `test/test-stage-variables.js`.'' Exercises `buildStageVariables` against a stub object (cp-actions prototype-patch applied to `{ stack, contextTiddler, wiki }`) ‚Äî no widget instantiation needed. Covers: base shape on empty stage; `currentTiddler` injection only when picked is non-empty; stack walk for `stage-N-picked`; context-tiddler from `this.contextTiddler`; `stage-preview-context` topmost-wins with fall-through; null-stage tolerance; extras merge over base; extras override (`currentTiddler` in particular); `hasOwnProperty` guard against prototype pollution. ''(5) New 7-spec `test/test-pillstrip.js` ‚Äî characterisation test.'' Written BEFORE the consolidation; same after. Boots each of filter/visibility/reach/field renderers against a minimal `wrappedDoc()` (fakeDocument elements enhanced with classList + dataset shims since neither ships natively on TW's TW_Element). Asserts: empty pills array ‚Üí no children rendered + popup class cleared; populated ‚Üí one `<span class="rcp-pill[+modifier]">chip√ó</span>` per pill; focused pill carries `rcp-pill-focused` only when widget.focus matches focusSection; reach/field carry their respective modifier class. The same spec passes byte-stably before and after `cp-pillstrip` lands ‚Äî proving DOM equivalence. ''(6) Cumulative test count: 100 cascade-palette specs / 1861 total specs / 0 failures.'' Up from 51 in 0.0.79 (Phase A baseline), 82 in 0.0.81 (Phase B sub-step). ''Touches:'' new `widgets/cp-pillstrip.js`, `widgets/cp-actions.js` (`_filterInScope` + extras param), `widgets/cp-leaders.js`, `widgets/cp-axes.js`, `widgets/cp-keyboard.js`, `widgets/cp-side-preview.js`, `widgets/cp-row-icons.js`, `widgets/cp-visibility.js`, `widgets/cp-views.js`, `widgets/cp-rendering.js`, `widgets/cp-stack.js`, `widgets/cp-firing.js`, `widgets/cp-filters.js`, `widgets/cp-field-pills.js`, new `test/test-stage-variables.js`, new `test/test-pillstrip.js`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.81 |2026-05-28 |''Phase B refactoring foundation ‚Äî shared `cp-utils` library + pure-function extractions for the constraint-pill subsystems. No behaviour change; all 1843 specs in the cumulative test edition pass byte-stably.'' Continuation of the 0.0.80 investigation-driven refactor. Three pieces consolidate: ''(1) New `widgets/cp-utils.js` ‚Äî stateless shared library.'' Exposes `parseNumOrNull` / `parseNumOrDefault` (previously instance methods on cp-items; now thin delegators), `sanitizeConstraintArg` (the strip-ctrl-chars / drop-brackets / cap-200 transformation that filter+visibility builders did inline), `buildConstraintInstance(meta, arg)` (the previously-duplicated body of `_buildFilterInstance` and `_buildVisibilityInstance` ‚Äî single source of truth for the instance shape), and `detectInputPrefix(text, filterMetas, visibilityMetas)` (the greedy-by-length matcher previously coupled to `this._loadFilterTiddlers` / `this._loadVisibilityTiddlers`). All four are tested in isolation against canned inputs. ''(2) `cp-filters` + `cp-visibility` consolidate.'' Both `_buildFilterInstance` and `_buildVisibilityInstance` were byte-identical pre-0.0.81 (sanitisation + same instance shape; only the field-name prefix differed in the loader). Now they both `return utils.buildConstraintInstance(meta, arg)`. Schema changes (e.g. Phase D's planned JSON `ca-bind` migration, or a future `<<argRaw>>` template variant) now land in one place. ''(3) `cp-input-prefix` shrinks to a wrapper.'' `_detectInputPrefix(text)` is now a 4-line passthrough to `utils.detectInputPrefix(text, this._loadFilterTiddlers(), this._loadVisibilityTiddlers())` ‚Äî the latter two calls were already cached by 0.0.80, so the wrapper is O(1) after first warm. ''(4) `cp-items` delegates `_parseNum*`.'' Same pattern ‚Äî instance methods kept for back-compat (so existing `this._parseNumOrDefault(f["ca-step"], DEFAULT_STEP)` call sites stay unchanged), bodies now `return utils.parseNum‚Ä¶`. ''(5) New te