|0.0.80 |2026-05-28 |''Phase A refactoring foundation ‚Äî adds tests, caches hot-path loaders, cleans dead duplicate, and documents the engine + dev workflow. No behaviour change.'' Outcome of the [[refactoring investigation|https://github.com/rimir-cc/tw-cascade-palette]] launched 2026-05-28: every change in this version is byte-stable across previously-rendered outputs; the first dependable test scaffold for the plugin lands here. ''(1) Caching the constraint-prefix loaders.'' `_loadFilterTiddlers` (cp-filters.js) and `_loadVisibilityTiddlers` (cp-visibility.js) were re-executing `wiki.filterTiddlers` + per-title `getTiddler` on every keystroke (4 reloads per keystroke between `_detectInputPrefix` and `_updateConstraintPrefixCue`). Now keyed on `wiki.getChangeCount()` mirroring `cp-row-icons.js`'s `_loadRowIcons` pattern ‚Äî cache returns the same array reference until a write bumps the counter. With shipped 4 filters + 2 visibilities the saving is tiny; with the typical kind / orga-palette-scale catalogue the per-keystroke cost was O(constraints), now O(1) until a write. ''(2) Pure-function exports for testability.'' `cp-axes` now exports `groupBy` and `sortGroups` alongside the previously-exported `parseChainSpec` / `layerSlug` / `evalKey` / `evalLabel` etc. `cp-row-icons` switches its `module.exports` shape from a bare patch function to `setup` with `setup.URL_PROTOCOL_RE` attached. `cp-views` extracts the inline ca-position field parser into top-level `parsePositionField(posRaw)` + `resolveEntryPositions(entryFields, slug)` helpers ‚Äî both call sites (`_evaluateLayer` and `_evaluatePositionedEntries`) collapse to one-line lookups. Same parsing semantics; the helpers are deterministic and testable. ''(3) First three Jasmine specs.'' `test/test-axes.js` covers `parseChainSpec` (null / empty / space-separated / JSON array / mixed / malformed JSON fallback / entries without title), `groupBy` (empty / multiple items / null-key collapse to `UNSET_KEY`), and `sortGroups` (`first-seen`/`asc`/`desc`/`enum` with unknowns). `test/test-row-icons-url.js` covers the URL allowlist regex (http / https / case-insensitive / ftp / ftps / mailto / tel accepted; bare hosts / file: / javascript: / data: / magnet: / vscode: / unstripped whitespace rejected). `test/test-views-position.js` covers parsePositionField + resolveEntryPositions including the two-slug precedence chain. ''Documents one pre-existing limitation:'' the `[:\n]` split conflicts with system-tiddler titles (`$:/...`) ‚Äî captured as a KNOWN test (won't accidentally regress) and slated for resolution via the upcoming JSON-shape position field. 51 specs, 0 failures locally; the full `tw-tests/test-edition` suite of 1812 specs passes. ''(4) Test-edition integration.'' `tw-tests/test-edition/tiddlywiki.info` now loads `rimir/cascade-palette` and `rimir/kind`. Run with `bin/tw test cascade-palette`. ''(5) Dead-code cleanup.'' `views/by-date.tid` had both `ca-view-source: [!is[system]!is[shadow]]` AND the identical `ca-view-roots: ‚Ä¶` on the next line ‚Äî `ca-view-source` is only read as a back-compat alias when `ca-view-roots` is absent (cp-views.js fallback chain). The duplicate line was dead. Deleted. ''(6) Settings tab rewritten as a config index.'' `settings.tid` was an ad-hoc mix of three knobs and two diagnostics buttons. Now it explicitly enumerates every `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/*` tiddler with its purpose, whether a UI row exposes it, and where to edit if not ‚Äî including the four advanced deep-search tuning knobs (max-depth, max-nodes, max-ms, search-fields-default) and the `entity-type-field` bridge. No new settings, just discoverable from one place. ''(7) New doc tiddlers per project standard.'' `doc/dev-workflow.tid` (section-order 25) covers the contributor surface: tag ‚Üí required fields ‚Üí worked examples table; local dev cycle; debugging action discovery; backwards-compat conventions; version-bump rules; testing patterns (gotchas fixture / wiki-test-spec / Jasmine spec). `doc/tw-internals.tid` (section-order 45) covers the engine internals: startup mounting, navigator routing, the `makeFakeWidget` invariant (and why it dodges [[tw-gotchas-widget-context#Custom fake widgets‚Ä¶|https://github.com/rimir-cc/tw-cascade-palette]]), stage stack + persistence, filter substitution, side-preview cache, axis-key memoisation, prototype-extension contract, hot-path inventory. ''(8) Confirmed-still-correct invariants (no code change).'' `proto.makeFakeWidget` correctly delegates to `this.makeFakeWidgetWithVariables` at cp-actions.js:206 ‚Äî central, used by all 24 fake-widget callsites. JSON state writes (cp-stack.js:131, cp-pick-presets.js:179, cp-axes.js:364) are all compact (no indents) so the filesystem-sync `.tid ‚Üí .json` flip from non-`text` newline-containing fields ([[tw-gotchas-filesystem-sync#Non-text field with newline‚Ä¶]]) is avoided. Legacy `tree-strategy` code is fully gone from cp-views.js ‚Äî only doc references remain. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-filters.js`, `widgets/cp-visibility.js`, `widgets/cp-axes.js`, `widgets/cp-row-icons.js`, `widgets/cp-views.js`, `views/by-date.tid` (delete duplicate), `settings.tid` (rewrite), new `doc/dev-workflow.tid`, new `doc/tw-internals.tid`, new `test/test-axes.js`, new `test/test-row-icons-url.js`, new `test/test-views-position.js`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. Test-edition wiki info updated to include cascade-palette + kind (not in plugin tree ‚Äî in `tw-tests/`). JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.79 |2026-05-28 |''Filter-based action discovery (`ca-applies`) ‚Äî actions can now surface on tiddler rows in tree views too, not only in the catalogue.'' Before: action discovery on a row required the row's emitting layer to declare `ca-layer-row-entity-type`; this set `item.entityType`, which `loadActionsForType` matched against `ca-entity-type`. Tree-view structure-layers (''By namespace'', ''By parent'', ''Hybrid'' inner layers) don't bind a row-entity-type, so the same person/team/task tiddler that surfaces a full action menu in ''Entries'' had no actions in tree views ‚Äî even though it's the same tiddler. The user's framing: ''register actions by filter against the row's tiddler, not against an entity-type label''. ''(1) New action field `ca-applies`.'' Filter evaluated with `<currentTiddler>` bound to the row's title; non-empty result ‚áí the action surfaces on that row regardless of view. Example: `ca-applies: [<currentTiddler>get[kind]match[person]]` surfaces wherever a tiddler's `kind` is `person`. Catalogue actions can keep their existing `ca-entity-type: person` AND add `ca-applies` ‚Äî both paths union (deduplicated by action title) so the same action shows up in Entries AND By namespace. ''(2) `loadActionsForType` extended.'' Discovery now runs both paths: catalogue (`ca-entity-type` matches the row's bound type, plus `*` globals) and filter (`ca-applies` non-empty for `<currentTiddler>` = `contextTitle`). New helper `actionAppliesViaFilter(actionTitle, contextTitle)` encapsulates the filter check + error logging. `entityType=null` is now a valid input ‚Äî skips the catalogue path and relies on `ca-applies` + globals only (used by tree-view SPACE handler). `ca-action-when` still narrows whichever path matched. ''(3) SPACE now opens actions on any tiddler row.'' `cp-keyboard.js` Space handler: when the picked row has a real tiddler title (not synthetic) ‚Äî with OR without an `entityType` ‚Äî it pre-flights `loadActionsForType(<resolved entityType>, picked.title)`. EntityType resolution covers three sources: ''row-bound'' (`picked.entityType` set by `ca-layer-row-entity-type` on the emitting layer ‚Äî Entries rows), ''stage-bound'' (filter-stage dynamic items inherit `stage.entityType` ‚Äî drill into Persons ‚Üí person rows; the item itself doesn't carry the type but the stage does), ''unbound'' (real tiddler rows in tree/flat views like ''By namespace'', ''By parent'', ''All tiddlers'' ‚Äî rely on `ca-applies` filter discovery + `*` globals only). If the preflight returns non-empty, push the action-menu stage; otherwise silent no-op (no empty menu pops up on rows that have no actions wired). The stage-bound case is the fix for "Space inside KIND ACTIONS sub-drill didn't open the next action menu, only Right did" ‚Äî both gestures now route through the same entityType resolution. Works the same way in catalogue and tree views ‚Äî the new filter path simply broadens what counts as "has actions". ''(4) Tab keyboard contract ‚Äî no longer drills.'' Audit confirmed Tab in code has been cycle-only for a while (cp-keyboard.js:51-58, `_cycleFocus`/`_jumpFocusGroup`), but docs still claimed "Tab drills" in several places. Tab now documented unambiguously: ''cycles focus between sections within the current group''; Shift-Tab ''jumps between the pill-group (top strips) and the main group (input/menu/details/preview)''. Only Right-arrow drills. ''(5) Docs.'' New FAQ entries: "Why don't I see person/team/task actions in tree views?", "How do I open the action menu on a row in a tree view?", "What's the difference between `ca-entity-type`, `ca-action-when`, and `ca-applies`?". Protocol doc gains `ca-applies` field entry + Worked example 5 (same action in catalogue AND tree views via dual fields, plus a pure-filter-bound action with no catalogue presence). Reference table gains `ca-applies` row, updates `ca-entity-type` description to clarify it's the catalogue path and `ca-action-when` to clarify it's the refinement filter. Architecture doc rewrites the `kind: "actions"` stage description to spell out the two-path discovery and unions; rewrites the Right-arrow / Space / Tab rows in the keyboard-router list. Welcome help is restructured around five gestures (with Tab explicitly noted as "cycle, never drill"). Keys help table updates Shift-Tab to "Jump between pill-group and main group", Right to mention tree containers, Space to mention `ca-applies` filter discovery. README.md + readme.tid + overview.tid + examples.tid + reference.tid + protocol.tid all updated for the new mental model. ''(6) Configured-field auto-derive ‚Äî a data-model plugin can bridge `ca-entity-type` to every view with one config tiddler.'' New config `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/entity-type-field` (engine ships NO default ‚Äî opt-in by a data-model plugin). When set to a field name, an action's `ca-entity-type: <X>` ALSO matches any row whose tiddler carries `<configured-field>: <X>` ‚Äî auto-derived `ca-applies` without per-action authoring. ''Why:'' catalogue plugins like orga-palette already declare `ca-entity-type: person` etc. and DON'T want to duplicate that information into a per-action `ca-applies` filter. A type-system plugin (`rimir/kind`) already knows the universal type-field convention (`kind.type`) used across every kind-instance in the wiki. Centralising the bridge there means: ''catalogue plugins stay simple'' (no per-action filter authoring); ''cascade-palette stays generic'' (engine reads the config; no field name baked in); ''every existing catalogue action surfaces in every view automatically'' on Space ‚Äî Entries, All tiddlers, By namespace, By parent, Hybrid, By date. ''Implementation:'' new constant `C.ENTITY_TYPE_FIELD_CONFIG`; `cp-stack.js` adds `_entityTypeField()` (reads the config text, trims) and `actionMatchesByConfiguredField(actionEntityType, contextTitle)` (returns true when the configured field on the row's tiddler equals the action's entity-type ‚Äî exact-match, no filter eval); `loadActionsForType` inserts the new check between the catalogue path and the `ca-applies` filter path. Skipped when the action's entity-type is `*` or unset, when the config is empty, or when there's no context title ‚Äî keeps the no-bridge default cost at one `getTiddlerText` per discovery call. ''Bridge plugin (`rimir/kind` ‚â• 0.1.50):'' ships a single new tiddler `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/entity-type-field` with text `kind.type`. Install kind ‚Üí every `ca-entity-type: <X>` action surfaces wherever `kind.type: <X>`. ''Caveat ‚Äî engine alone is no-op.'' Without a bridge plugin (or a manually-authored config tiddler), ''All tiddlers'' / ''By namespace'' / ''By parent'' / ''Hybrid'' / ''By date'' still silent-no-op on Space when no `ca-applies` action and no `*` global matches. The cascade-palette engine itself ships only one specialised action (`actions/tag-tree-node-delete.tid`, `ca-entity-type: tag-tree-node`) and no `ca-applies` actions ‚Äî these views need either a catalogue+bridge combination (e.g. orga-palette + kind) or per-action `ca-applies` filters to light up. ''Uninstall path:'' delete the config tiddler ‚Üí auto-derive disabled ‚Üí behaviour reverts to catalogue + explicit `ca-applies` + globals only. ''(7) Visual actionability indicator on every row.'' `_maybeAppendActionPreview` (the existing `‚ÜíN` badge) used to gate on `item.entityType`, so only rows with row-bound entityType (Entries view + drill-stage dynamic items with stage.entityType set) showed the count. ''Now:'' the badge gates on `item.title && !item.isSynthetic`, exercises the same three-source entityType resolution as the SPACE handler (row ‚Üí stage ‚Üí null), and surfaces the badge whenever `loadActionsForType(<resolved>, title)` returns > 0. Rows in ''All tiddlers'' / ''By namespace'' / ''By parent'' / ''Hybrid'' / ''By date'' now show `‚ÜíN` whenever actions match via the catalogue + configured-field + `ca-applies` paths. The badge is the user's "Space will do something here" cue. New CSS class ''`rcp-row-actionable`'' is stamped on the same rows (cheap left-edge marker ‚Äî `box-shadow: inset 3px 0 0 #6366f1;` light, `#818cf8` dark, brighter when selected) so even when the badge sits offscreen on a long row, the leading edge tells you actionable rows from inert ones at a glance. ''Performance:'' counts are still memoised per-render by `(entityType, title)` key (existing `_actionPreviewCountCache` in `renderResults`), so re-rendering on every keystroke is cheap for already-evaluated rows. The hot path is the first render after a stage push ‚Äî bounded by `getMaxResults` (default 30 rows) and the count of registered actions (typically <50 plugin-wide). The configured-field bridge is a getTiddler+field-compare (no filter eval), so adding it to the resolution chain doesn't materially change cost. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-stack.js` (`loadActionsForType` rewrite, `actionAppliesViaFilter` new helper, `isActionApplicable` unchanged), `widgets/cp-keyboard.js` (Space handler ‚Äî accepts no-entityType rows + preflight), `doc/faq.tid`, `doc/protocol.tid`, `doc/architecture.tid`, `doc/examples.tid`, `doc/overview.tid`, `doc/reference.tid`, `help/keys.tid`, `help/welcome.tid`, `readme.tid`, `README.md`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.78 |2026-05-28 |''Followup: 0.0.77's focus restore after Ctrl-Alt-‚Üµ didn't actually work ‚Äî keystrokes still leaked to the story river.'' The fix went through `setFocus(this.focus)`, but that helper short-circuits at line 1171 (`if (this.focus === section)`) ‚Äî it only updates the `data-focus` attribute, never re-calls the DOM element's native `.focus()`. Since we capture the focus section ''before'' the copy and restore to ''the same section'' afterwards, the early-return path always fired. The textarea's `.select()` had taken the actual DOM focus, but the palette's logical `this.focus` state still said "input", so setFocus saw no work to do ‚Äî and the DOM focus stayed on `<body>`. ''Fix:'' new private helper `_refocusSection(name)` that mirrors `setFocus`'s dispatch table but bypasses the early-return ‚Äî it always resolves the DOM element for the named section and calls its native `.focus()`. `_copyPayloadToClipboard` now defers `_refocusSection(section)` via `setTimeout(0)` so the textarea's removal settles first. Falls back to the input element if the recorded section is no longer reachable (its strip was removed etc.). ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-row-icons.js` only. JS module changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.77 |2026-05-28 |''Fix: Ctrl-Alt-‚Üµ copy-payload was stealing focus from the palette.'' TW core's `$tw.utils.copyToClipboard` works by creating a transient `<textarea>`, appending it to `<body>`, calling `.select()` / focus on it to make the selection authoritative for `execCommand("copy")`, then removing the node. The `.select()` step takes focus away from the palette's search input; when the textarea is removed afterwards, focus lands on `document.body`, not back where it came from. Effect on the user: after Ctrl-Alt-‚Üµ on a üåê row, the input no longer accepts keystrokes ‚Äî typing went to the browser tab instead of narrowing the cascade. ''Fix:'' `_copyPayloadToClipboard` now snapshots the active focus section before invoking `copyToClipboard`, then re-calls `setFocus(section)` on the next tick (via `setTimeout(0)`) so the textarea's removal settles first. The user keeps typing exactly where they were. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-row-icons.js` (focus-restore wrapper around the copy call). JS module changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.76 |2026-05-28 |''Row-icon secondary action ‚Äî Ctrl-Alt-‚Üµ + new `copy-payload` built-in.'' Generalises the row-icon protocol with an optional ''secondary'' gesture wired to ''Ctrl-Alt-‚Üµ'', alongside the existing primary Alt-‚Üµ. ''(1) Protocol extension.'' Three new optional fields on row-icon-tagged tiddlers: `ca-row-icon-alt-action` (wikitext fired by Ctrl-Alt-‚Üµ), `ca-row-icon-alt-message` (built-in JS dispatch key ‚Äî same vocabulary as `ca-row-icon-message`), `ca-row-icon-alt-hint` (tooltip text). The shipped üåê icon now declares `ca-row-icon-alt-message: copy-payload` + `ca-row-icon-alt-hint: Copy URL to clipboard`. ''(2) New built-in message.'' `copy-payload` ‚Äî delegates to `$tw.utils.copyToClipboard(payload)` (TW core helper that handles both the modern Clipboard API and the legacy execCommand fallback, and emits a tm-notify on success/failure). Can be used in any row-icon ‚Äî primary OR alt slot. ''(3) Generalised fireRowIcon.'' Signature gains a `mode` argument (`"primary"` default, `"alt"` for Ctrl-Alt-‚Üµ). In `alt` mode it reads `icon.altMessage` / `icon.altAction` instead of the primary fields. Action wikitext receives a new `<<row-icon-mode>>` variable (`"primary"` / `"alt"`) so a single action can branch on which gesture fired it. ''(4) Keyboard.'' Tier-2c Enter handler in `cp-keyboard.js` now branches on `e.ctrlKey` in the Alt-‚Üµ block: bare Alt-‚Üµ ‚Üí mode `"primary"`, Ctrl-Alt-‚Üµ ‚Üí mode `"alt"`. Silent no-op when the icon has no action for the requested mode (so Ctrl-Alt-‚Üµ on a primary-only icon doesn't surprise-close the palette by falling through to fireSelected). ''(5) Discoverability.'' New `HINT_MENU_ROW_ICON_ALT` constant ‚Äî `Tab section ¬∑ Alt-‚Üµ open ¬∑ Ctrl-Alt-‚Üµ copy ¬∑ ‚Üµ fire ¬∑ ‚Ä¶`. Footer hint dispatcher (`_renderHint`) detects whether the focused row's ''primary'' icon declares an alt action and swaps the hint accordingly. Hover tooltip on each glyph now shows the alt hint on a second line, suffixed with ` ¬∑ Ctrl-Alt-‚Üµ`. ''(6) Docs / help.'' Reference doc gains the Ctrl-Alt-Enter keybinding row + 3 new `ca-row-icon-alt-*` field rows + the `copy-payload` message entry. Protocol doc gains the secondary-gesture protocol entries + Ctrl-Alt-‚Üµ description on the URL row-icon. Architecture doc's Firing subsection rewritten to describe both modes + the built-in messages. Readme bullet mentions both gestures on üåê. ''`?`-help'' (`help/keys.tid`) gains two new rows: `Alt-‚Üµ` + `Ctrl-Alt-‚Üµ`. New FAQ entry "How do I copy a URL to the clipboard from a search result?" answers the exact question this feature was built for. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-row-icons.js` (4 alt fields wired through load+expose+fire+tooltip), `widgets/cp-keyboard.js` (Ctrl-Alt-‚Üµ branch), `widgets/cp-constants.js` (HINT_MENU_ROW_ICON_ALT), `widgets/cascade-palette-widget.js` (hint dispatcher checks for alt gesture), `row-icons/url.tid` (alt-message + alt-hint), `readme.tid`, `settings.tid` is unchanged, `doc/reference.tid` (1 key + 3 fields + 1 message), `doc/protocol.tid` (alt-action / alt-message / alt-hint entries + Ctrl-Alt-‚Üµ URL paragraph), `doc/architecture.tid` (Firing subsection rewrite), `doc/faq.tid` (new clipboard entry), `help/keys.tid` (2 new key rows). JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.75 |2026-05-28 |''Hotfix: 0.0.74 over-suppressed `ca-actions` on tree-row drills ‚Äî Enter / Ctrl-Enter on a folder in ''By Namespace'' / ''Hybrid'' stopped navigating to the tiddler.'' `fireSelected` was sending all drill-row Enter presses through `drillSelected`, and 0.0.74 gated the drill-preflight to skip template ca-actions on Right-arrow ‚Äî but the same gating also killed the action-fire path that Enter relied on, so Enter on a tree container drilled silently instead of navigating. ''Fix:'' `fireSelected` now treats template-sourced drill rows (`_actionsFromRowTemplate: true`) as leaves on Enter ‚Äî calls `fireLeafAction` (which fires the `$action-navigate` and respects Ctrl-Enter keep-open), exactly like Enter on a regular leaf. Right-arrow keeps the structural-only behaviour from 0.0.74 (no navigate, just descend into children). Clean three-keystroke separation on tree containers: ''Right'' = drill, ''Enter'' = navigate (+ close), ''Ctrl-Enter'' / ''Shift-Enter'' = navigate (keep palette open). Rows that carry their own intentional `ca-actions` (kind plugin's draft-seeding etc.) continue to fire on Right-arrow as before ‚Äî only template-sourced actions are gated. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-firing.js` `fireSelected` drill branch. JS module changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.74 |2026-05-28 |''Fix: Right-arrow on a tree-view container row also fired its `ca-view-row-actions` (typically `$action-navigate`), navigating to the tiddler as a side-effect of drilling.'' Regression introduced by 0.0.66's drill-preflight feature, which fires `ca-actions` on every drill-enter so the kind plugin can seed drafts with defaults before the create-fields drill renders. The preflight didn't distinguish between ''row tiddler's own intentional ca-actions'' (kind's draft-seeding use case ‚Äî should fire on drill) and ''ca-actions synthesised from a `ca-(view|layer)-row-actions` template'' (typically `$action-navigate` intended for Enter ‚Äî should NOT fire on drill). Effect on the user: pressing Right-arrow on a folder in ''By Namespace'' / ''Hybrid'' would push the tree-stage AND navigate the storyline to the folder tiddler, opening it in the story river unintentionally. ''Fix:'' `cp-views.js` `_evaluateLayer` now stamps `item._actionsFromRowTemplate = true` on rows whose `ca-actions` came from `layer.rowActions`. `cp-firing.js` `drillSelected` skips the preflight when that flag is set ‚Äî Right-arrow on tree containers is now purely structural (descend into children), and Enter still fires the template's `$action-navigate` for navigate-to behaviour. Backward-compatible: kind's draft-seeding (and any author-shipped drill row carrying its own `ca-actions`) keeps firing on Right-arrow as before. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-views.js` (stamp flag), `widgets/cp-firing.js` (gate preflight). JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.73 |2026-05-28 |''Fix: ''By Date'' view (and every axis chain) was bucketing every row under the first wiki tiddler's date.'' Critical bug in `cp-axes.js` `evalKey` / `evalLabel` ‚Äî `wiki.filterTiddlers(filter, widget)` was called WITHOUT a source argument, so TW core (`filters.js:377`) fell back to `wiki.each` (= all non-system tiddlers). For the shipped axes which use bare per-row filters like `[get[created]format:date[YYYY]]`, the filter then enumerated EVERY tiddler's `created` field, formatted each as YYYY, and `evalKey` took `r[0]` ‚Äî whichever tiddler happened to be first in the wiki's iteration order. Result: every row in the ''By Date'' view ended up bucketed under that one tiddler's year / month / day, regardless of its own `created` date. ''Fix'' ‚Äî both `evalKey` and `evalLabel` now pass `[tiddlerTitle]` (resp. `[key]`) as the source argument to `wiki.filterTiddlers`, making each per-row filter operate on the right input. Filters that explicitly anchor with `<currentTiddler>` keep working because the variable is still bound; bare filters now also work because the input source is the row. Same fix benefits the parametric `by-field` axis and any user-shipped axes that omit `<currentTiddler>`. Docs (`doc/reference.tid`) updated to spell out the dual binding contract: ''both'' the filter's input source ''and'' `<currentTiddler>` resolve to the row tiddler (resp. bucket key for labels). ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-axes.js` (two filterTiddlers calls + comment), `doc/reference.tid` (ca-axis-key + ca-axis-label rows), `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. JS module changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.72 |2026-05-28 |''Row-icon eligibility fix + visual tuning.'' Follow-up to 0.0.71. ''(1) Bug fix ‚Äî icons now show across every view.'' `computeRowIconsForItem` gated on `item.isItem && item.rawTitle`, but those fields are only stamped by `evaluateFilterStage` (cp-actions.js) for dynamic filter-stage items. Tree-view rows (''By Namespace'', ''By Parent'', ''By Date'', ''Hybrid'' layers ‚Äî everything built via `cp-views.js`'s `_buildCascadeItem` factory) only carry `item.title` (no `rawTitle`, `isItem` defaults to `false`). Effect pre-fix: the üåê row-icon appeared ONLY on dynamic filter results, NOT on tree-view rows ‚Äî exactly the views that surface user-owned tiddlers carrying URL fields. Alt-‚Üµ also no-op'd on those rows because the keyboard branch reads `item._rowIcons` which was always empty. ''Fix'' ‚Äî gate is now `!item.isSynthetic && (item.rawTitle || item.title)`. Synthetic items (`ca-items-from` JSON, confirm-stage placeholders, axis-picker wrapper rows) still skip; everything backed by a real tiddler ‚Äî entries, actions, tree rows across every view, dynamic items ‚Äî gets the icon when the row's tiddler matches. `fireRowIcon` reads the same `rawTitle || title` fallback so Alt-‚Üµ resolves the row title even when only `item.title` is set. Architecture doc gains a ''Row eligibility'' subsection spelling out which row kinds are eligible vs excluded. ''(2) Visual tuning ‚Äî strip is smaller and tucked under the row.'' CSS reduces the strip's `font-size` from 12px to 6px (per user feedback that the original glyph was too prominent), `gap` between glyphs from 6px to 3px, `padding` per glyph from `1px 3px` to `0 1px`, and `border-radius` from 3px to 2px. The row's flex `gap: 10px` was leaking between the wrapped name line and the icon strip ‚Äî cancelled with `margin-top: -8px` so the strip sits flush against the row text. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-row-icons.js` (gate + Alt-‚Üµ title fallback), `styles.tid` (size + gap), `doc/architecture.tid` (Row eligibility paragraph). JS module changed ‚Äî restart required (CSS-only tuning is hot). |
|0.0.71 |2026-05-28 |''Row icons + Alt-‚Üµ open-URL.'' New extension point that surfaces small affordance glyphs in a footer strip beneath any tiddler-bearing row ‚Äî without crowding the name / value slots. ''(1) Tag-based registration.'' New tag `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/row-icon` (constant `C.ROW_ICON_TAG`). Each tagged tiddler declares: `ca-row-icon-key` (symbolic id ‚Äî `url` triggers the built-in field-scanning resolver; other keys rely on the applies filter), `ca-row-icon-glyph` (display character / emoji), `ca-row-icon-hint` (tooltip), `ca-row-icon-applies` (filter ‚Äî `<currentTiddler>` is the row's tiddler title; non-empty result = icon shows; ignored for the `url` key), `ca-row-icon-payload` (optional filter resolving the value bound to `<<payload>>` when firing), `ca-row-icon-action` (optional wikitext actions fired with `<<payload>>` + `<<row-icon-key>>` + stage variables), `ca-row-icon-message` (optional built-in JS dispatch key ‚Äî currently only `open-url` is recognised), `ca-row-icon-primary` (`yes` = preferred Alt-‚Üµ target when multiple icons apply), `ca-row-icon-order` (display order in the strip). ''(2) Shipped URL icon.'' `row-icons/url.tid` ships with key `url` + glyph üåê + message `open-url`. The built-in resolver reads `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/url-fields` (new config tiddler, default `url`, space-separated) and walks the configured fields on each row's tiddler in order ‚Äî first value matching `/^(?:https?|ftp|ftps|mailto|tel):/i` wins. The strip renders only on rows whose URL resolved, so unrelated tiddlers stay clean. ''(3) Alt-‚Üµ keyboard gesture.'' New tier-2c branch in `cp-keyboard.js` before the regular Enter dispatch: when the selected row has at least one row-icon, Alt-‚Üµ (no Ctrl / no Shift) fires the row's ''primary'' icon via `fireRowIcon`. Falls through to regular Enter dispatch when no icons resolved, so users who reflex-press Alt-‚Üµ on a normal row get the default action rather than a silent no-op. ''(4) Click gesture.'' Mousedown on the glyph fires that specific icon and `stopPropagation`s ‚Äî the row's own selection / fire handler does not also run. Lets users open the URL without keyboard. ''(5) `fireRowIcon` dispatcher.'' Both Alt-‚Üµ and click route here. If `icon.message === "open-url"`, `window.open(payload, "_blank", "noopener,noreferrer")` runs via the document's `defaultView`. If `icon.action` is set, it runs through `invokeViaNavigator` with `<<payload>>`, `<<row-icon-key>>`, and the standard stage variables. Both fire when both are set. ''(6) Discoverability ‚Äî hint footer.'' `HINT_MENU` is replaced by new `HINT_MENU_ROW_ICON` (`Tab section ¬∑ ‚Üë‚Üì select ¬∑ ‚Üí drill ¬∑ Alt-‚Üµ open ¬∑ ‚Üµ fire ¬∑ Esc input ¬∑ hold Ctrl detail`) when the selected row has at least one icon resolved. So the Alt-‚Üµ gesture is visible the moment focus lands on a row that supports it. ''(7) Caching.'' `_loadRowIcons` caches the registry by `wiki.getChangeCount()`. The change hook (`cascade-palette-widget.js`) drops the cache when any row-icon-tagged tiddler is created/modified/deleted OR when the URL_FIELDS_CONFIG tiddler changes. Per-item resolution runs every render ‚Äî generic filter-based icons cost one `wiki.filterTiddlers` per row per icon, so author your `ca-row-icon-applies` to return fast (e.g. `[<currentTiddler>has[field]]` rather than a graph walk). The built-in `url` key bypasses filterTiddlers entirely (pure field reads). ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-constants.js` (`ROW_ICON_TAG`, `URL_FIELDS_CONFIG`, `HINT_MENU_ROW_ICON`), `widgets/cp-row-icons.js` (new ‚Äî ~220 LOC: registry loading + caching, URL resolution, per-item icon list, fire dispatch, DOM rendering), `widgets/cp-rendering.js` (`_appendResultRow` calls `_renderRowIcons` after match snippets), `widgets/cp-keyboard.js` (Alt-‚Üµ branch in tier-2c Enter handler), `widgets/cascade-palette-widget.js` (subsystem install, hint dispatch checks `_rowIcons`, change-hook invalidates row-icon cache on tag / URL_FIELDS_CONFIG change), `styles.tid` (`.rcp-row-icons` strip + `.rcp-row-icon-glyph` + primary variant + light/dark modes; `.rcp-row-has-icons` triggers row flex-wrap), new `row-icons/url.tid`, new `config/url-fields.tid`. Docs: `readme.tid` (row icons bullet), `settings.tid` (URL fields setting), `doc/architecture.tid` (Row icons section + `row-icons/` in tree), `doc/reference.tid` (`row-icon` tag row, 9 `ca-row-icon-*` field rows, Alt-Enter keybinding row, URL_FIELDS_CONFIG setting), `doc/protocol.tid` (full Row icons section with two worked examples ‚Äî Linear ticket + edit-raw). JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.70 |2026-05-28 |''Tag-based auto-attach for the side-preview pane + multi-candidate pills.'' Two coupled extensions of the side-preview protocol introduced in 0.0.52. ''(1) Tag-based registration.'' New tag `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/side-preview` (constant `C.SIDE_PREVIEW_TAG`). Tiddlers wearing the tag declare a preview candidate that auto-attaches whenever the row's resolved context matches the candidate's `ca-preview-applies` filter (evaluated with `<currentTiddler>` bound to the context). Fields on a tagged tiddler: `ca-preview-template` (defaults to the tagged tiddler's own title ‚Äî the tagged tiddler IS the template), `ca-preview-applies` (filter; empty = always matches), `ca-preview-name` (pill label), `ca-preview-title` (caption above body), `ca-preview-order` (sort key among tag candidates; default 100). This is parallel to ‚Äî not a replacement for ‚Äî the existing per-menu `ca-preview-template` on entries/actions: both contribute candidates to the same pill row. Use case: a single tagged tiddler `kind/palette/preview/instance-view` with `ca-preview-applies: [<currentTiddler>has[kind.type]]` makes the kind-instance preview show up automatically in any browse list where the selected row has `kind.type`, without each consumer plugin re-declaring `ca-preview-template`. ''(2) Multi-candidate pills with ‚Üê/‚Üí navigation.'' When more than one candidate applies at the same time (per-menu + tag-matched, or several tag-matched), a horizontal pill row appears at the top of the preview pane ‚Äî one pill per candidate. The active pill is highlighted; clicking a pill switches; ‚Üê/‚Üí when the preview pane has focus cycles forward/backward (wraps at both ends). With a single candidate the pill row is suppressed entirely via the `:empty` CSS selector ‚Äî the pane looks identical to the pre-pill UX, no churn for existing consumers. Hint footer dynamically swaps from `HINT_PREVIEW` to new `HINT_PREVIEW_PILLS` (`Tab section ¬∑ ‚Üê‚Üí switch preview ¬∑ ‚Üë‚Üì scroll ¬∑ Esc input`) when multiple candidates apply, so the gesture is discoverable. ''(3) Activation paths broadened.'' `_attachPreviewToStage` now activates the pane in three cases ‚Äî was just one. (a) Per-menu template declared (existing behaviour). (b) ''Tag-only opt-in'' ‚Äî the entry/action sets `ca-preview-context` or `ca-preview-per-row` without an explicit template; the pane activates and populates from tagged candidates only. Lets a browse-list opt into auto-attach without having to pick a "default" template. (c) Inheritance ‚Äî sub-drills that don't declare any preview state inherit the parent's template, BUT the context is now LOCKED to the row that was drilled into (not the sub-stage's selected row). This fixes a latent bug where action-menu sub-drills mistakenly re-resolved the preview context to the action's own tiddler title; the entity being acted upon is now correctly retained as the preview anchor. ''(4) Field on cascade items.'' `ca-preview-name` parses into `previewName` on the item object (`widgets/cp-items.js`). Used as the pill label when the row's preview-template ends up alongside tag candidates. ''(5) Cache invalidation.'' The change hook now also drops the tagged-previews cache (`_taggedPreviewsCache`) AND the rendered preview cache when any side-preview-tagged tiddler is created, modified, or deleted ‚Äî so swapping out a template tiddler or adding a new candidate plugin reflects on the very next render without manual reload. ''(6) Stage record fields.'' New optional stage fields populated by `_attachPreviewToStage`: `_previewMenuName` (the pill label for the menu candidate), `_previewActiveIdx` (zero-based pointer into the resolved candidate list; ‚Üê/‚Üí mutates this). Backward-compatible ‚Äî existing fields (`_previewTemplate`, `_previewContext`, `_previewTitle`, `_previewPerRow`) keep their meaning. ''(7) DOM addition.'' New `.rcp-preview-pane-pills` row above `.rcp-preview-pane-title` in the side-preview pane (`cascade-palette-widget.js`). Light + dark themes via the existing `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` blocks. Active-pill outline uses the same `data-focus="preview"` selector as the pane's left-edge highlight, so focus state is consistent. ''(8) Documentation.'' `cp-side-preview.js`'s module-header comment is rewritten to spell out the two-mechanism resolution model and the candidate-list / pill-navigation flow. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-constants.js` (`SIDE_PREVIEW_TAG`, `HINT_PREVIEW_PILLS`), `widgets/cp-side-preview.js` (rewritten ‚Äî new helpers `_loadTaggedPreviews` / `_applicableTaggedPreviews` / `_resolvePreviewCandidates` / `_defaultPreviewName` / `_setPreviewActiveIdx` / `_cyclePreviewActive` / `_previewHasMultipleCandidates`, `_activePreviewContext` extended, `_renderSidePreview` rebuilt around candidate list, `_handleKeydownPreview` gained ‚Üê/‚Üí cycling, `_hideSidePreview` clears pill row), `widgets/cp-firing.js` (`_attachPreviewToStage` rewritten ‚Äî 3 activation paths + inheritance lock), `widgets/cp-items.js` (`previewName`), `widgets/cascade-palette-widget.js` (pill DOM, hint dispatch checks multi-candidate, change-hook invalidates tagged cache), `styles.tid` (pill row + light/dark variants). JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.69 |2026-05-28 |''Two small but high-leverage protocol additions for create/edit flows.'' (1) ''New `<<keep-open>>` action variable.'' Action wikitext now sees `<<keep-open>>` = `"yes"` when fired via Ctrl-Enter (or when the leaf carries `ca-after-fire: keep`), `""` otherwise. Lets a single save-leaf branch on "mass-create / batch entry" vs "create-and-close" without needing two distinct rows. ''Why:'' the previous workaround was duplicating leaves with different `ca-after-fire` values ‚Äî but Ctrl-Enter is a per-keystroke modifier, not an authoring-time decision. This exposes the modifier to the action so the SAME leaf can do "create + navigate" on Enter and "create + stay" on Ctrl-Enter. First consumer: kind plugin's "Save as ‚Ä¶" leaf (kind 0.1.47). ''Implementation:'' `vars["keep-open"]` set in `fireLeafAction` (after `ca-after-fire="keep"` upgrade, before `pop` early-return so the popped leaf sees the right value) and in `fireSelected`'s `isItem` branch (so dynamic entity actions also see it). Other paths (toggle, drill, number/date) don't fire `ca-actions` wikitext, so no plumbing needed there. (2) ''DEL on a bound-field row now clears the field.'' Previously DEL on a `ca-bind-tiddler` + `ca-bind-field` row was a no-op (the existing DEL handler only fired for `isOverridden` rows or `isItem` real-tiddler rows). Now: row with `bindTiddler` + `bindField` + not `isItem` ‚Üí DEL unsets the field. Whole-field bindings ‚Üí field removed entirely (action-deletefield idiom: `removeFields[field] = undefined` in the Tiddler constructor drops the key). Sub-path bindings (`ca-bind-path`) ‚Üí write `""` into the JSON node (omitting a key in a schema-shaped JSON isn't always semantically what callers want). New `clearBoundField` helper in cp-items.js. After clear, the stage is recomputed + re-rendered so the row's displayed value updates immediately. (3) ''Pure-display warning leaves (no `ca-actions` + `ca-after-fire: keep`) now no-op on Enter instead of closing.'' Pre-0.0.69, `fireSelected` checked `picked.kind === "leaf" && picked.actions` ‚Äî leaves without actions FELL THROUGH past the leaf branch and landed in the catch-all `if (!keepOpen) this.close("preserve")` at the bottom of `fireSelected`, dismissing the palette. The `ca-after-fire: keep` field was never read for action-less leaves because it's only consulted inside `fireLeafAction`, which the gated check skipped. ''Symptom:'' kind plugin's title-collision / constraint-violation / title-formula-empty warning rows (which have `ca-after-fire: keep` precisely to stay open) closed the palette when the user pressed Enter on them ‚Äî losing the draft context. ''Fix:'' new explicit early-return at the top of the leaf branch: `if (picked.kind === "leaf" && !picked.actions && picked.afterFire === "keep") return`. Enter on such a row does nothing ‚Äî palette stays open with the row visible. The user fixes the underlying field, the warning row swaps out, the real Save leaf swaps in (per the host plugin's `~`-fallback filter chain), and Enter saves normally. (4) ''Edit-mode commit now returns focus to the menu.'' Editing a text/number/date row pushed focus from the menu into the input (the input is repurposed as the value editor). On Enter-commit (or Esc-cancel), the input was restored to the query string but focus stayed there ‚Äî the user then had to Tab/ArrowDown back to the menu just to arrow-navigate to the next row. `exitEditMode` now calls `setFocus("menu")` as its last step. The row stays selected (`selectedIndex` is restored from `savedSelectedIndex` earlier in the function), so the user lands back exactly where they were ‚Äî arrow keys, DEL, Ctrl-‚Üë/‚Üì, re-Enter all work without re-grabbing focus. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-firing.js` (3 lines ‚Äî `keep-open` var in two fire paths, `afterFire="keep"` lifted above var-build; `setFocus("menu")` at end of `exitEditMode`), `widgets/cp-items.js` (`clearBoundField`), `widgets/cp-keyboard.js` (DEL handler ‚Äî new clause between `isOverridden` and `isItem`), `plugin.info` version. JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.68 |2026-05-27 |''Per-layer grouping axes ‚Äî chain year/month/day, status, prefix, etc. inside any structure-layer.'' New tag `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/axis` for reusable derive-key specs. An axis declares `ca-axis-key` (filter mapping a row to a bucket key), optional `ca-axis-label` (key ‚Üí display label), and a sort mode (`first-seen` / `asc` / `desc` / `enum` + `ca-axis-sort-keys`). A structure-layer may now declare `ca-layer-axes` (or `ca-view-axes` for implicit-layer views) listing axis tiddlers ‚Äî the chain runs at the top of the descent, with each level filtering the source set down by the axis's key. Past the chain, the layer's own `roots`/`children` filters take over (so axes ''compose with recursive trees'': year‚Üímonth‚Üíday ‚Üí then descend the layer's tag-tree under each day). New ''Structure-strip axis pills'' make this configurable per session: yellow ''by'' / ''‚Üí'' pills per layer carry the active chain, a dashed ''+'' pill appends, Backspace removes, Shift-‚Üê/‚Üí reorders, Enter on a chain pill swaps it. State persists in `$:/state/rimir/cascade-palette/layer-axes/<slug>` (survives reload but not filesystem-synced ‚Äî declared `ca-layer-axes` is the default the user can reset to). ''Performance:'' axis keyFn results are memoised in a closure cache invalidated on `wiki.getChangeCount()` ‚Äî first touch fills, subsequent re-renders are O(visited rows). ''Shipped:'' 5 axes (`by-year-created`, `by-month-created`, `by-day-created`, `by-year-modified`, parametric `by-field`) and a `views/by-date` demo. ''Mindmap lib reuse:'' `groupBy`/`sortGroups` come from `$:/plugins/rimir/mindmap/lib/grouped-tree.js` when installed, with a tiny inline fallback otherwise (mindmap is a soft-dep now). ''Reset-on-edit:'' any chain mutation (add / replace / remove / reorder) resets the stage stack to root before re-rendering. The deeper `parentPath` entries are bucket keys produced by the OLD chain ‚Äî under the NEW chain they'd point at non-existent bucket