|0.0.67 |2026-05-27 |''Session-stack persistence ‚Äî Shift-Esc / action-fire close now "freezes" the current stack so the next open resumes where you left off.'' Workflow continuity: a long drill (Manage kinds ‚Üí kind ‚Üí field ‚Üí constraint picker) is no longer lost when you Shift-Esc to attend to something else, or when a leaf action opens a tiddler and closes the palette. ''Mental model:'' `close()` paths fall into two camps. ''Preserve'' (saves stack to `$:/temp/rimir/cascade-palette/saved-stack`): Shift-Esc (explicit "park"), action-fire close (default leaf-action exit via `afterAction` keepOpen=false, AND the `fireSelected` fallback close at line 170). ''Reset'' (clears the saved tiddler): plain Esc at root via the input handler (the user walked all the way back ‚Äî explicit "I'm done"), `popStage` walking off root, backdrop-click close (the user clicked away ‚Äî same "done" intent). The two callers that should NEVER restore ‚Äî `openPaletteAtEntry` (callers explicitly point us at one entry) and OPEN_ENTRY_MESSAGE (same path) ‚Äî pass `{ fresh: true }` to `openPalette`, which skips the restore step regardless of saved state. ''Why $:/temp:'' TW filesystem syncers skip the `$:/temp/` namespace, so the saved tiddler dies with the page (session-only) without reaching for `sessionStorage` ‚Äî same pattern the rest of the workspace uses. No browser-storage API surface. ''Serialization shape:'' the stack is a JSON array of stage descriptors. We strip `items` / `results` (recomputed on next access) and break out at the first `confirm` or `actions` stage ‚Äî those reference closure-captured action strings or a parent-picked tiddler that may be gone, so dropping them and everything above keeps the restored chain internally consistent. ''Re-lookup on restore:'' filter stages have `entityDefaultActions` snapshot at build time; on restore we re-call `lookupEntityDefaultActions(stage.entityType)` so a wiki where action tags changed since save doesn't misroute Enter on a dynamic item. ''What happens on stale state:'' if the user closes, deletes a tiddler the saved stack references, then re-opens ‚Äî `recomputeStage` on the top stage produces an empty `results` list (no items match the now-broken parent). User Escs back, hits a working ancestor. Predictable; not pretty. ''Skip-trivial guard:'' `persistStack` declines to save a stack of length ‚â§ 1 (root-only) ‚Äî there's nothing to resume, no point keeping a `$:/temp` tiddler around. ''Filters / visibilities / reaches / fields'' were already preserved across close/open (predates this change; see openPalette comment line 922). This patch is purely additive: it adds stack-level resume on top of the existing per-session constraint persistence. ''Manual reset:'' user wants a fresh start mid-session ‚Üí walk back to root (Esc, Esc, ‚Ä¶) then Esc once more ‚Üí close-without-preserve fires ‚Üí next open is fresh. Or just delete `$:/temp/rimir/cascade-palette/saved-stack` directly. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-constants.js` (new `SAVED_STACK_TIDDLER` const), `widgets/cp-stack.js` (4 new helpers: `serializeStack`, `persistStack`, `clearSavedStack`, `restoreSavedStack`), `widgets/cascade-palette-widget.js` (`openPalette` accepts `{fresh}`, `openPaletteAtEntry` forces fresh, `close` accepts a `reason`), `widgets/cp-keyboard.js` (Shift-Esc ‚Üí `close("preserve")`), `widgets/cp-firing.js` (`afterAction` close-on-fire ‚Üí `close("preserve")`, `fireSelected` fallback ‚Üí same). All other `close()` callers (backdrop click, Esc-at-root, popStage past root) default to reset ‚Äî no edits needed. JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.66 |2026-05-27 |''Two changes ‚Äî one new capability + one bug-class fix.'' (1) ''Drill rows can now carry `ca-actions` that fire on drill-enter'' (before the next stage is pushed). Previously only `kind:"leaf"` items fired `ca-actions`; drill items just navigated. Use case: pre-seeding a draft tiddler with field defaults when the user clicks "+ New X" so the about-to-open drill renders with values already filled in. Author-side contract: actions must be idempotent ‚Äî backing out and re-entering re-fires them. Backward-compatible: drill items without `ca-actions` behave exactly as before. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-firing.js` (`drillSelected`). (2) ''String-array bind type now respects TW list-format quoting.'' Previously toggle on/off detection and the inline value display used naive whitespace-split, which mangled entries with spaces (e.g. tiddler titles like `Echo Fox` became two pills "Echo" and "Fox"). Now parses via `$tw.utils.parseStringArray` (respects `[[...]]` quoting) and bound-drill rows with `ca-bind-type: application/x-string-array` display as comma-joined captions (e.g. `brown fox, Bar` not `[[brown fox]] Bar`). Mirrors scribe v0.1.2's same migration. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-firing.js` (`fireToggle`), `widgets/cp-items.js` (`isToggleOn`), `widgets/cp-rendering.js` (`_renderBoundDrillValue` new STRING_ARRAY_TYPE branch). JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.65 |2026-05-27 |''Fix: detail drawer was dead code on confirm stages (Ctrl-hold did nothing).'' Long-standing bug uncovered while testing the kind plugin's delete-kind confirm consequence: `renderDetails` (cp-rendering.js:521) returned early via `if (!picked || !picked.title) { this.hideDetail(); return; }`. But `buildConfirmStage` synthesizes Confirm/Cancel items with `title: ""` (empty by design ‚Äî they're synthetic placeholders, not entity references). So for ANY confirm stage, `picked.title` was empty ‚Üí early-return ‚Üí drawer hidden ‚Äî making the consequence-banner block (`if (stage.kind === "confirm" && stage.consequenceText)`) at line 550 unreachable. Architecture doc claimed "consequence text shows in the detail drawer" but that surface was effectively broken ‚Äî users had no way to see the consequence even with Ctrl-hold or always-on. ''Fix:'' the early-return now only triggers when `!picked.title && stage.kind !== "confirm"`. Confirm stages reach the consequence-banner code, which renders `stage.consequenceText` in `.rcp-details-consequence`. Empty-title non-confirm rows still skip the drawer (preserves existing behaviour). ''Companion change:'' the header element (`<div class="rcp-detail-title">‚Ä¶</div>`) is now skipped when `picked.title` is empty ‚Äî confirm stages would otherwise render an empty header above the consequence banner. Stage title (the leaf's name, e.g. "üóë Delete this kind") remains visible in the breadcrumb at the top of the popup. ''Combined effect with 0.0.64:'' Confirm row's hint (inline subtitle) shows the consequence on every confirm stage, AND Ctrl-hold (or details-always-on) now opens the drawer showing the same consequence in `.rcp-details-consequence` styling. Belt + suspenders. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-rendering.js` (two small guards in `renderDetails`). JS module changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.64 |2026-05-27 |''Confirm-stage Confirm row now shows ca-confirm-consequence as its hint ‚Äî visible inline, not only in detail drawer.'' Previously the consequence text was rendered only in the detail drawer (which is hidden by default and surfaces with Ctrl-hold or via `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/details-always-on`). Result: users who triggered a confirm-leaf saw a stage with just "Confirm" / "Cancel" rows ‚Äî no indication of what's being confirmed. The kind plugin's "üóë Delete this kind" particularly suffered: its dynamic consequence text spelling out instance count / orphan warning was effectively hidden. ''Fix:'' `buildConfirmStage` (cp-stack.js:190) now sets `confirmItem.hint = spec.consequence || ""`. Confirm row renders with the consequence as its inline subtitle ‚Äî visible without Ctrl, on any confirm stage. The full `consequenceText` is STILL kept on the stage object for the detail drawer (when shown via Ctrl or always-on config). ''Backwards compatible:'' any caller that set `ca-confirm-consequence` now gets it inline-visible as a bonus; behaviour for callers without consequence is unchanged (hint stays empty). ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-stack.js` (single field change). JS module changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.63 |2026-05-27 |''Fix: confirm-path popStage now skips when the action chain replaced the stack.'' The confirm sub-stage's leaf-fire branch (cp-firing.js:66) called `this.popStage()` ''unconditionally'' after `invokeViaNavigator` ran the leaf's actions. That worked for the typical "delete a thing then return to the previous stage" pattern. But it broke when the action chain itself replaced the stack ‚Äî e.g. `$action-sendmessage $message="rimir-cascade-palette-open-entry" entry="‚Ä¶"` calls `openPaletteAtEntry`, which calls `openPalette()` (rebuilds `this.stack = [buildRootStage()]`) then drills into the entry ‚Üí stack is `[root, entry-stage]`. The confirm stage is GONE from the stack at this point. But the unconditional `popStage()` then ran on the NEW stack and popped the entry-stage that the actions just installed, leaving `[root]`. User reported: "after Confirm Delete I end up above Manage kinds" ‚Äî i.e. at root, having lost the entry drill they expected to land on. ''Fix:'' guard the post-fire pop with `if (this.topStage() === stage) { this.popStage(); }` ‚Äî if our confirm stage isn't on top anymore, the actions handled navigation themselves and we don't pop. ''Why the identity check works:'' stack entries are objects, so `===` matches only the same stage object. If openPaletteAtEntry rebuilt the stack, the new root + entry-stage objects are different instances, so the check correctly skips. Standard pattern: actions either (a) do nothing stack-related ‚Üí confirm stage still on top ‚Üí pop runs (preserves existing behaviour); (b) replace the stack ‚Üí confirm stage gone ‚Üí pop skipped. ''Backwards compatible:'' all existing ca-confirm callers (without stack-rewriting actions) hit branch (a), behave exactly as before. ''Note for action authors:'' if your confirm leaf's actions send OPEN_ENTRY_MESSAGE (or otherwise call `openPalette()`), you no longer need to compensate ‚Äî the engine respects the rewrite. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-firing.js` (3-line guard in the `stage.kind === "confirm"` branch). JS module changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.62 |2026-05-26 |''In-palette Help system + per-row side-preview opt-in.'' Two coupled features. ''(1) Help entry.'' New ''Help'' entry (tag `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/entry`, glyph ‚ùì) drills into 7 core help sections ‚Äî Welcome, Keys, Pills, Search, Entries, Authoring, Plugins. Each section is a tiddler tagged ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/help`'' with standard cascade-item fields (`ca-name`, `ca-icon`, `ca-group`, `ca-order`, `ca-hint`, `ca-kind: leaf`) and a wikitext body. Enter on a row navigates to the help tiddler in the story river for full-width reading. Body renders in the side-preview pane as the user navigates ‚Üë/‚Üì. Reachable via ''`?` leader'' (new). ''(2) Live cheat-sheets.'' The ''Keys'', ''Pills'', and ''Entries'' help sections render `<$list>`-driven tables over the existing protocol tags ‚Äî every leader / entry currently in the wiki appears automatically. Plugin-contributed leaders / pills / entries surface without help-side edits. ''(3) Plugin contributions.'' Any plugin can ship a single help tiddler tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/help` with `ca-group: Plugin: <slug>`. The Plugins sub-drill (one row at top-level) lists them. Bounded contribution surface ‚Äî one tiddler per plugin, ~30 lines. ''(4) Per-row side-preview opt-in.'' New entry field ''`ca-preview-per-row`'' ‚Äî when `yes`, the side preview re-resolves its context to the currently-selected row's title on every ‚Üë/‚Üì keystroke (was: context stamped once at drill-time). Inherits into sub-drills via `_attachPreviewToStage` so the Help ‚Üí Plugins drill keeps live-preview behaviour without each level re-registering a template. Generic feature ‚Äî any browse-list drill where each row is a distinct document benefits. Single hook in cp-keyboard.js (arrow handlers) + cp-side-preview.js (`_activePreview` reads per-row context) + cp-firing.js (`_attachPreviewToStage` inherits per-row from parent). ''(5) Hint footer + empty-results text.'' `HINT_INPUT` gained `¬∑ ? help` suffix; empty-results row reads ''"No results ‚Äî ? for help"'' (was just "No results"). ''New tiddlers:'' `entries/help.tid`, `leaders/help.tid`, `help/preview-template.tid`, `help/welcome.tid`, `help/keys.tid`, `help/pills.tid`, `help/search.tid`, `help/entries.tid`, `help/authoring.tid`, `help/plugins.tid`. ''Touches:'' `cp-constants.js` (`HELP_TAG`, hint suffix), `cp-items.js` (`previewPerRow` on items), `cp-firing.js` (`_attachPreviewToStage` inheritance), `cp-side-preview.js` (`_activePreview` per-row), `cp-keyboard.js` (arrow re-render hook), `cp-rendering.js` (empty text), `styles.tid` (`.cp-help-pane` block + dark-mode variant), `doc/protocol.tid` (new Help section), `doc/reference.tid` (HELP_TAG + ca-preview-per-row rows). JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.61 |2026-05-26 |''Fix: Reach leaders `d` / `g` were no-ops after 0.0.60.'' The mutual-exclusion rewrite of `_pushReach` (cp-reach-pills.js) cleared `this.reachPills = []` but ''never pushed the new instance'' afterwards ‚Äî so pressing `d` or `g` evicted any existing pill and added nothing, leaving the strip empty and `_activeReachMode()` permanently returning `"local"`. Reach was dead. Added the missing `this.reachPills.push(instance)` + `this.reachFocusIdx = 0` reset right after the array reset, so the new pill actually lands. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-reach-pills.js`. JS module changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.60 |2026-05-26 |''Reach pills now mutually exclusive + tiddler-field matching + strip rename Fields ‚Üí Search-in.'' Three small follow-ups to 0.0.59. ''(1) Reach mutual exclusion.'' Pushing any Reach pill now evicts every other Reach pill ‚Äî "Here" and "Everywhere" can't both be active. They overlap semantically (Everywhere subsumes Here) so coexistence was redundant and confusing. `_pushReach` now clears the array before pushing; `_activeReachMode` simplified accordingly. ''(2) Tiddler-field fallback in the matcher.'' Search-in pills can now expose tiddler fields, not just cascade-item properties. New helper `_resolveMatchableField` (cp-actions.js) walks two layers: cascade-item property first (fast, populated at item-build time); on miss, `wiki.getTiddler(item.title).fields[<key>]` is consulted. Array-typed fields (`tags`, list-fields) flatten to space-separated strings for substring matching. Both filterByQuery and deepWalk consume the same resolver. ''Shipped pill:'' ''üìÑ Text'' ‚Äî matches the tiddler body. Authors can drop in `tags`, `caption`, `modifier`, or any custom field the same way (no protocol or JS change required). ''(3) Strip label rename.'' The violet pill row's `::before` label is now ''Search-in'' (was "Fields") ‚Äî clearer about what the pills control. Internal property / method / tag names retain the original `field` spelling for code stability; the user-facing label is the only surface that changed. Leader `a` and the `field-add` leader were updated to push the new Text pill alongside the existing five. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-reach-pills.js` (mutex), `widgets/cp-actions.js` + `widgets/cp-deep-search.js` (`_resolveMatchableField` + consumers), `styles.tid` (strip label), `reach/here.tid` + `reach/everywhere.tid` (help text), `leaders/field-add.tid` (push Text too), new `field/text.tid` pill, `doc/deep-search.tid` + `doc/protocol.tid` + `doc/reference.tid`. JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.59 |2026-05-26 |''Search controls split out of the Filter strip into two dedicated pill rows: Reach + Fields.'' The 0.0.58 attempt to wire deep-search into the Filter strip conflated two distinct concerns ‚Äî filters narrow the data set, search controls configure HOW search works ‚Äî so they get their own strips with the same push/remove pill grammar as filters / visibility / view. ''Reach strip'' (teal accent, tag `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/reach`) holds two shipped pills: ''üîç Here'' (walk the subtree under the current stage) and ''üåê Everywhere'' (walk from the active view's root). Both can coexist; the wider scope wins. ''Fields strip'' (violet accent, tag `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/field`) holds one pill per searchable item field ‚Äî ''üè∑ Name'', ''üí° Hint'', ''üìù Description'', ''‚Ü™ Aliases'', ''üîé Search-text''. Multiple pills active = matcher reads the union of those fields, ignoring per-row `ca-search-fields` and global default. No field pills active = per-row / global default kicks in. ''Leaders renamed:'' `d` ‚Üí push Reach: Here, `g` ‚Üí push Reach: Everywhere, `a` ‚Üí "Fields: Match anywhere" (pushes all 5 shipped Field pills at once). ''Multi-match collection.'' filterByQuery + deepWalk now collect ALL matches across the active field set into `item._matches` (not just the first). Renderer iterates `_matches` and surfaces one snippet line beneath the row for each match in a non-displayed field (description / aliases / searchText / author-defined). Name / hint matches still highlight inline ‚Äî the snippet pass doesn't duplicate them. Lets the user see WHY every result is in the list, even when the matching content isn't normally visible. ''New tag families:'' `REACH_TAG`, `FIELD_TAG`. ''New messages:'' `rimir-cascade-palette-add-reach`, `-add-field`, `-reset-reach`, `-reset-fields` (with param `reach` / `field` naming the tiddler). ''New modules:'' `widgets/cp-reach-pills.js` (~190 lines, mirrors cp-filters.js shape), `widgets/cp-field-pills.js` (same). ''New tiddlers:'' 2 reach pills, 5 field pills, 3 renamed leaders (reach-here / reach-everywhere / field-add). ''Removed:'' `filters/search-deep-here.tid`, `filters/search-deep-root.tid`, `filters/search-anywhere.tid` and the `ca-search-mode` / `ca-search-fields-override` filter-pill protocol (moved to dedicated subsystems). ''Touches:'' `cp-constants.js` (4 new constants + tags + hints), `cascade-palette-widget.js` (2 DOM elements + listeners + setFocus branches + render-on-open + message handlers + state init + require), `cp-keyboard.js` (REACH_KEY_DESC + FIELD_KEY_DESC + dispatch + `_pillsCycle` + `_isPillFocus` + Enter Tier-2c exclusion), `cp-stack.js` (`applyQueryToStage` calls `_activeReachMode`), `cp-actions.js` (`filterByQuery` collects `_matches`), `cp-deep-search.js` (`_matchItemAll`, fieldOverride from `_activeFieldNames`, `_activeReachMode`-aware doc string), `cp-firing.js` (replay path uses `_activeReachMode`), `cp-filters.js` (drops `_activeSearchMode` / `_activeSearchFields` / mode pass-through), `cp-rendering.js` (iterates `_matches` for snippets). ''CSS:'' two new strip rules with teal + violet accents, light + dark variants. JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.58 |2026-05-26 |''Deep-tree search via filter pills.'' Today's search input filters only the ''current stage's'' visible rows ‚Äî to find a row two drills deep you had to drill there first. New: push the ''üîç Deep here'' or ''üîç Everywhere'' pill and typing walks every drill reachable from the current stage (or from the active view's root), surfacing matches with a breadcrumb prefix (`Kinds ‚Üí Task ‚Üí fields  priority: enum ‚Üí`). Picking a deep result ''replays the path'' ‚Äî the cascade pushes the intermediate stages exactly as you'd have done by hand, then engages the picked row (drill or fire). Any `<<parent-picked>>` / `<<stage-N-picked>>` action wikitext sees the same context it would have under a manual drill, so deep picks don't break actions. The two deep pills are mutually exclusive; both survive stage push/pop so a follow-up search after a pick continues to work without re-pushing. ''Configurable searched fields.'' Each cascade item can now declare ''`ca-search-fields`'' (space-separated, default reads `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/search-fields-default` = `name hint`) ‚Äî extends the matcher beyond name/hint to any string-valued item field. New optional item-keys: ''`ca-description`'' (longer-form), ''`ca-aliases`'' (alternate names), ''`ca-search-text`'' (catch-all bag, not displayed). ''Match highlight + snippet line.'' The matched substring is wrapped in `.rcp-match` on the row name / hint; for matches in non-displayed fields (description / aliases / searchText) a muted ''snippet line'' renders below the row with 24 chars before + 40 after the match window, prefixed by which field surfaced the row. ''Match anywhere pill.'' ''üîé Anywhere'' pill overrides every row's `ca-search-fields` and matches against ALL recognised text fields at runtime ‚Äî composable with the deep pills (Deep + Anywhere = widest possible search). ''Author opt-out:'' ''`ca-search-skip: yes''' excludes a row AND its subtree from the deep walk. Default auto-skip for text/number/date/toggle/confirm row kinds. ''Caps:'' walks are bounded by max-depth (4), max-nodes (800), max-ms (80) ‚Äî config tiddlers at `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/deep-search-*`. Cap fires append a truncation hint row. ''New module:'' `widgets/cp-deep-search.js` (BFS over synthetic stages via existing `buildFilterStage` / `_buildRowsForView` primitives). ''Touches:'' `cp-items.js` (5 new item keys), `cp-actions.js` (filterByQuery walks per-item search-fields, stamps `_match`), `cp-filters.js` (`ca-search-mode` / `ca-search-fields-override` pass-through; `_activeSearchMode` / `_activeSearchFields` helpers; mutually-exclusive eviction for deep-mode pills), `cp-stack.js` (`applyQueryToStage` branches on `_activeSearchMode`), `cp-firing.js` (`replayDeepPath` + `_drillOnItemForReplay` + `_locateItemInStage`; fireSelected and drillSelected intercept on `_path`), `cp-rendering.js` (`_path` breadcrumb prefix + `_match` highlight wrap + snippet line + truncation-sentinel row class), `styles.tid` (`.rcp-match` / `.rcp-row-breadcrumb` / `.rcp-row-snippet` / `.rcp-row-deep-truncated` rules, light + dark), `cascade-palette-widget.js` (require new module). ''Activation:'' three new leader keys ‚Äî ''`d`'' (deep here), ''`g`'' (everywhere), ''`a`'' (anywhere). ''Three gestures on a deep result'' ‚Äî Enter = navigate + execute (fire / drill); Right-arrow = navigate + drill (no-op on plain leaves); ''Space = navigate + pin'' ‚Äî replays the path and selects the row at its natural stage but does NOT fire / edit / open action menu. Safe gesture for inspecting destructive matches before committing. ''New tiddlers:'' 3 pills (deep-here / deep-root / anywhere), 3 leaders, 4 configs (max-depth / max-nodes / max-ms / search-fields-default), 1 doc page (`doc/deep-search.tid`). JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.57 |2026-05-26 |''Row-level move action protocol ‚Äî `ca-on-move-up` / `ca-on-move-down`.'' Two new optional fields on cascade items, fired when the user presses Ctrl-‚Üë / Ctrl-‚Üì on the focused row (menu focus only ‚Äî bare ‚Üë/‚Üì keep their selection-nudge semantics). Mirrors the existing `ca-on-delete` plumbing: synthetic JSON-array rows whose "reorder" means mutating the parent tiddler can now declare a wikitext action that swaps the element with its neighbour. cp pre-bumps `stage.selectedIndex` by ¬±1 before firing so the user's selection follows the moved row through the change-hook's stage recompute (which preserves selectedIndex when results length is unchanged). No action declared ‚Üí Ctrl-‚Üë/‚Üì falls through to bare ‚Üë/‚Üì (selection nudge), preserving back-compat. ''Bounds:'' if the row can't move (top/bottom of stage), selectedIndex is left in place but the action still fires ‚Äî the action itself is responsible for being a no-op when at the boundary (the kind plugin's `kind.cascade-move-field` filter-guards against out-of-range swaps, so spurious end-of-list Ctrl-‚Üë/‚Üì are silent). ''Implementation:'' `cp-items.js` reads `onMoveUp` / `onMoveDown` off the item; `cp-keyboard.js` `_handleKeydownMenu` adds a Ctrl-‚Üë/‚Üì branch before the bare arrow handlers ‚Äî when the focused row has the action declared, pre-bumps selectedIndex, builds standard stage substitution variables (`picked` = row title, `parent-picked`, `stage-N-picked` walk), invokes via `invokeViaNavigator`. ''Use case:'' rimir/kind 0.1.31's field list ‚Äî Ctrl-‚Üë/‚Üì on a field row reorders the kind's `kind.fields` JSON array, which propagates to the form preview (field rendered in array order) and to instances created after the move. JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.56 |2026-05-26 |''Side preview pane: make embedded widgets truly interactive (keys + reactive refresh).'' Two bugs the side-preview shipped with in 0.0.52 ‚Äî both broke the "live form" use case where the right pane hosts an `$edit-text` form whose values feed the cascade flow on the left. ''(1) Enter / Space stolen by the cascade.'' The popup's keydown listener routed every bubbled key to `handleKeydown`, which in turn fires the focused cascade row on Enter regardless of where the event originated. So clicking into a form input inside the preview gave the input browser focus (correctly ‚Äî the existing mousedown handler skips focus-stealing for inputs/buttons/etc) but the very next Enter fired the cascade menu instead of committing the input. Same hazard for Space (toggles cascade-side selection), arrows (move cascade selection), etc. ''Fix:'' new helper `_keydownTargetIsInsidePreviewWidget(e)` returns true when the keystroke originated inside the sidePreview pane AND the target is an editable widget (`input` / `textarea` / `select` / `button` / `a` / `contentEditable`). The popup's keydown listener now early-returns in that case, letting the event reach the widget natively. Escape is explicitly excluded so the user can always pop focus back to the cascade input from inside the preview. ''(2) Reactive nodes never re-evaluated.'' `wiki.makeWidget()` builds a STANDALONE widget tree ‚Äî it sets `parentWidget` on the new widget but does NOT add the widget as a child of the root widget's `.children` array. So when the wiki fires the change event, the root widget's auto-refresh-cycle never reaches the preview's tree. Inputs inside the tree kept appearing to type (they own their own DOM and listen to their own bind tiddler change) but every conditional / filter expression / `<%if function[viol-min]%>` validation row around them stayed frozen on whatever it computed at render time. Concrete symptom (kind plugin): a text field with `required, min:3` showed "‚õî min 3" forever, regardless of what the user typed. ''Fix:'' the `_renderSidePreview` cache now stashes the rendered `widgetNode`. The wiki change hook, when the change DIDN'T touch the template/context tiddler (which would force a full rebuild), now calls a new `_refreshSidePreviewOnChange(changes)` that dispatches `widgetNode.refresh(changes)` into the cached tree. Reactive nodes re-evaluate; the DOM updates in place; the input keeps focus and selection because the underlying $edit-text widget is itself refresh-stable. ''Touches:'' `cp-side-preview.js` (cache adds `widgetNode`; new `_refreshSidePreviewOnChange` + `_keydownTargetIsInsidePreviewWidget` methods), `cascade-palette-widget.js` (keydown listener routes to new helper before falling to `handleKeydown`; change hook calls refresh for non-invalidating changes). JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.55 |2026-05-26 |''Leader idle-window default 200ms ‚Üí 500ms.'' The shipped default for `ca-leader-idle-ms` (the pause after the leader key before actions fire) was too tight ‚Äî 200ms barely covers a deliberate finger-lift, so leaders sometimes fired during multi-char input or fast typing felt jumpy. Bumped to 500ms. Affects only the default ‚Äî leaders that explicitly set `ca-leader-idle-ms` are untouched. Doc tiddlers (`reference.tid`, `protocol.tid`) updated to match. JS module changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.54 |2026-05-26 |''New widget message `rimir-cascade-palette-open-entry` opens cp drilled into a named entry.'' Companion to `rimir-cascade-palette-open` ‚Äî takes an `entry` param naming a `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/entry`-tagged tiddler, opens the palette (resets to root if already open), looks the entry up in the just-computed root stage's results, and calls `drillSelected()` as if Tab had been pressed on it. Reuses every existing drill path (filter stage / items-from / tree-container) so behaviour is consistent with manual navigation. ''Use case:'' shipping plugins (e.g. ''rimir/kind'') can declare a leader tiddler with `ca-leader-actions: <$action-sendmessage $message="rimir-cascade-palette-open-entry" entry="$:/.../my-entry"/>` so a single keystroke after Ctrl-Space jumps straight into the entry's drill, skipping the find-the-right-row step at the root. Also reachable from any wikitext context via `<$action-sendmessage>` ‚Äî e.g. an EditorToolbar button can open cp at a specific entry from a tiddler view. ''Implementation:'' new constant `OPEN_ENTRY_MESSAGE` in `cp-constants.js`; new method `CascadePaletteWidget.prototype.openPaletteAtEntry(entryTitle)` in `cascade-palette-widget.js` that calls `openPalette()` then iterates the root stage's `results` to find the entry by title, sets `selectedIndex`, calls `drillSelected()`; new handler in `addEventListeners` parallel to the existing `OPEN_MESSAGE` handler (both `event.param` and `event.paramObject.entry` accepted). ''Silent no-op'' when (1) `entry` param missing/empty or (2) entry is not visible in the active view's root stage (hidden by visibility filters, wrong view scope, etc.) ‚Äî opens cp at root and stays there rather than throwing. ''Why not a leader-side `ca-leader-target-entry` field'' (rejected option A): the message form is more general ‚Äî any wikitext can invoke it (toolbar buttons, sidebar items, action chains, hotkeys via `KeyboardEvent`‚Üí`$:/core/ui/Buttons/control-panel`-style binds), not just leader-keys. The leader case is just one client of the message. JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.53 |2026-05-25 |''`ca-on-commit` action on text / number / date rows.'' New optional field that fires action wikitext AFTER a successful edit-mode commit, with `<<picked>>` bound to the value the user just typed. Lets single-shot text rows chain a create action onto the user's input ‚Äî e.g. ''+ Create new kind‚Ä¶'' captures a key with one Space-type-‚Üµ sequence and immediately fires `$action-createtiddler`, instead of needing a separate state tiddler + "Save" leaf and a multi-keystroke walk. ''Bind-less rows supported'' ‚Äî a text row with `ca-on-commit` but no `ca-bind-tiddler` is a pure value capture: nothing is written to a field; the value lives only in the `<<picked>>` variable for the action's lifetime. ''Implementation:'' `cp-items.js` reads the new `onCommit` field off the cascade item; `cp-firing.js`'s `exitEditMode` invokes the action via `invokeViaNavigator` with the standard stage substitution variables (`picked` = committed value, `parent-picked` = stage's outer pick, plus `stage-N-picked` walk) ‚Äî same scope `ca-actions` sees on a regular leaf. Only fires on successful commit (Esc skips, invalid-input retry skips). Used by ''rimir/kind'' for its ''+ Create new kind‚Ä¶'' row. JS module changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.52 |2026-05-25 |''Side preview pane + rename of Ctrl-hold drawer "preview" ‚Üí "detail".'' Two coupled changes. ''(1) Rename.'' The Ctrl-hold drawer below the result list was inconsistently called "preview" (CSS classes, hint footer text) and "details" (internal JS ‚Äî `detailsOpen`, `_detailsCache`, `HINT_DETAILS`, `findTemplatesFor`, `renderDetails`). All user-facing surfaces unified to "detail" so the word "preview" can refer exclusively to the new right-pane. CSS class renames: `.rcp-preview` ‚Üí `.rcp-detail-drawer`, `.rcp-previewing` ‚Üí `.rcp-showing-detail`, `.rcp-preview-title` ‚Üí `.rcp-detail-title`, `.rcp-preview-fields` ‚Üí `.rcp-detail-fields`, `.rcp-preview-empty` ‚Üí `.rcp-detail-empty`, `.rcp-preview-body` ‚Üí `.rcp-detail-body`. JS identifier `this.previewEl` ‚Üí `this.detailEl`; method `hidePreview` ‚Üí `hideDetail`. HINT_INPUT / HINT_MENU footer text "hold Ctrl preview" ‚Üí "hold Ctrl detail". No protocol-level field renames ‚Äî `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/template` tag and `ca-template-applies` filter keep their names (they describe the detail drawer's content). Touches 9 JS files + styles.tid. ''(2) Side preview pane.'' New right-column pane that an entry/action can register at drill time via three optional fields: ''`ca-preview-template`'' (title of the wikitext tiddler to render; required), ''`ca-preview-context`'' (filter evaluated in the parent stage's substitution scope ‚Äî `<<picked>>`, `<<parent-picked>>`, ‚Ä¶; first result becomes the preview's `<<currentTiddler>>`; default `<<picked>>`), ''`ca-preview-title`'' (optional caption). At every drill site (`drillSelected`'s 4 push points + the Space-on-typed-row push in `_handleKeydownMenu`), the new `_attachPreviewToStage` helper reads these fields off the picked row, evaluates the context filter, and stamps `_previewTemplate` / `_previewContext` / `_previewTitle` onto the freshly-built stage record. The topmost stage carrying `_previewTemplate` controls the pane ‚Äî deeper stages inherit it, so the user "stays in" the preview throughout a multi-stage sub-tree (e.g. editing a kind's fields one by one keeps the kind-form preview pinned). The resolved context value is also exposed to deeper stages' substitution scope as ''`<<stage-preview-context>>`'' so action wikitext / filter expressions inside the subtree can reach for "what we're talking about". ''Layout.'' `.rcp-popup` is now flex-row at the outer level with two children: `.rcp-cascade-col` (everything that used to be in the popup ‚Äî breadcrumb, pill strips, input, results, detail drawer, hint, perf footer) and `.rcp-preview-pane` (hidden by default; revealed when `.rcp-popup` carries `rcp-showing-preview`). When the pane is showing, both columns get `flex: 1 1 50%` ‚Äî the cascade visually shrinks to the left half. Popup-width config (`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/popup-width`) is unchanged; the split is purely a CSS flex artefact. ''Focus.'' New focus section ''`preview`'' joins the main cycle (input ‚Üí menu ‚Üí detail ‚Üí preview ‚Üí input) only when the pane is visible. Esc returns to input; arrow-up/down let the browser scroll natively. Mousedown on the pane background grabs focus, but clicks on inputs / buttons / links inside the rendered template pass through (the template is interactive ‚Äî widgets bubble events normally). New constant `HINT_PREVIEW`. ''Rendering.'' `_renderSidePreview` parses the template tiddler's body, builds a widget tree with `currentTiddler: <previewContext>`, mounts into `.rcp-preview-pane-body`. Cached by `(depth, contextTitle, templateTitle)` so keystroke-driven cascade redraws don't re-render the preview. Wiki-change hook invalidates the cache when either the template tiddler or the context tiddler changes ‚Äî so editing the kind's field list (the context tiddler) makes the form preview re-render live. ''New file:'' `widgets/cp-side-preview.js` (~140 lines). ''Touches:'' `cp-items.js` (3 new fields on the cascade item), `cp-firing.js` (`_attachPreviewToStage` helper + 4 push-site wires), `cp-keyboard.js` (Space push wire + main-cycle entry + Tier-3 dispatch case), `cp-actions.js` (`stage-preview-context` exposure in `buildStageVariables`), `cp-rendering.js` (call to `_renderSidePreview` from `renderStage`), `cp-constants.js` (`HINT_PREVIEW`), `cascade-palette-widget.js` (DOM restructure into `cascadeColEl` + `sidePreviewEl`, mousedown/focus listeners, setFocus validation + dispatch, hint dispatch, close-hides-pane, change-hook cache invalidation), `styles.tid` (popup ‚Üí flex-row, cascade-col + preview-pane rules, light + dark variants). JS modules changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.51 |2026-05-25 |''Fix: sub-path writes silently converted host tiddlers from `.tid` to `.json` file format.'' `writeBoundValue`'s sub-path branch (cp-items.js) was using `JSON.stringify(root, null, 4)` ‚Äî pretty-printed JSON with 4-space indents and newlines. TW's `generateTiddlerFileInfo` (core-server/filesystem.js:222-228) classifies any non-text field containing control characters (incl. `\n` = 0x0A) as "unsafe" and switches the host tiddler to `application/json` file serialization instead of `.tid`. So every cascade-mode sub-path edit to a JSON-encoded field (kind plugin's `kind.fields`, etc.) silently orphaned the `.tid` file on disk and wrote a `.json` file next to it. Reproduced: `my-wiki/tiddlers/_system/config/rimir/kind/types/project.json` exists (no `project.tid`), kind.fields stored as `"[\n    {\n        \"key\": ..."`. Changed to `JSON.stringify(root)` ‚Äî compact single-line JSON, no control chars, `.tid` format stable across edits. ''Migration:'' existing tiddlers that were already converted to `.json` stay as `.json` until the user manually deletes the `.json` file and re-saves the tiddler (TW reads `.json` and `.tid` equivalently ‚Äî same tiddler, different storage; no data loss). New edits on `.tid`-stored tiddlers stay `.tid`. JS module changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.50 |2026-05-25 |''Enter on text / number / date rows enters edit mode (symmetric with Space) + new `ca-on-delete` row action.'' Two related ergonomic fixes that emerged from the kind plugin's cascade-mode create flows. ''Enter on editable rows'' ‚Äî `fireSelected` (cp-firing.js) had explicit branches for leaf / drill / toggle / dynamic-filter-item kinds and a "else close palette" fall-through. Text / number / date rows fell through, so Enter closed the popup without engaging the row ‚Äî the user had to know Space was the only path into edit mode. Now Enter on a text / number / date row calls `enterEditMode` (same as Space). Note: Enter on a text row IN edit mode is unaffected (commits the value via `_handleKeydownEdit`); Enter in menu focus is what changed. ''Why not just teach users Space?'' Create flows ("+ Add new field‚Ä¶", "+ Create new kind") read as drill-style entry points ‚Äî users press Enter expecting engagement. The Space-only path was a surprising trap. ''`ca-on-delete` row action.'' New optional field on JSON cascade items: when DEL (or Backspace) is pressed on a row with `ca-on-delete`, the action wikitext fires (with `<<picked>>` / `<<parent-picked>>` substitutions). If `ca-on-delete-consequence` is also set, DEL pushes a confirm-stage with that consequence text before firing ‚Äî same model as `ca-confirm` on leaves. Used by the kind plugin's field rows so DEL on `priority ¬∑ enum` removes that field from `kind.fields` directly, without first drilling into the field-edit stage and finding the "üóë Delete this field" leaf. ''Priority:'' takes effect before the built-in restore-default (overridden settings) and delete-tiddler (entity row) DEL handlers, since synthetic JSON-item rows aren't either of those. New `onDelete` and `onDeleteConsequence` fields on the cascade item shape (cp-items.js). DEL handler in cp-keyboard.js's `_handleKeydownMenu` now checks for `onDelete` before falling through to the built-in paths. JS module changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.49 |2026-05-25 |''Leader pill row + per-view scope for leaders + Structure pills scroll horizontally.'' Leaders (the typed-key + idle-window gestures shipped in 0.0.27) get a visible surface and an extension hook. ''New leader strip'' sits between the Structure strip and the input ‚Äî one pill per visible leader, label is the key chip (purple-filled, monospace) followed by the leader's name. Hidden via `rcp-has-leaders` when no leader is visible. Activation paths are symmetric: typed-gesture path (type the key, idle 200ms) and pill path (Tab into the strip, ‚Üê/‚Üí select, ‚Üµ/Space fire). Pill click also fires. Focused pill renders the leader's name + help + key + idle window + view scope + actions + tiddler title into the details drawer (reusing `_renderLeaderHelp`, now shared between the typed-gesture and pill paths). ''Per-view scope.'' New optional field ''`ca-leader-views`'' on a leader tiddler ‚Äî a filter producing view titles. Empty / missing = global (always available, unchanged). Non-empty = leader is visible iff the active view's title is in the filter's result. Affects both surfaces ‚Äî the pill row hides the leader AND the typed-gesture stops matching it. None of the four shipped leaders set this field (they all remain global), but the mechanism is now available for domain plugins to ship view-specific leaders without polluting unrelated views. ''Tab cycle:'' leader joins the pill group at the end (visual order: preset ‚Üí visibility ‚Üí filter ‚Üí view ‚Üí viewconfig ‚Üí leader ‚Üí input ‚Üí menu ‚Üí details). ''Keyboard:'' new `LEADER_KEY_DESC` descriptor reuses the unified `_handleKeydownPillStrip` (Enter/Space fires, ‚Üê/‚Üí selects, Esc returns to input, Home/End not wired). ''Wiki change hook:'' invalidates the leader cache + re-renders the strip when any leader-tagged tiddler changes / is deleted (mirrors the existing preset-change handler). ''New methods:'' `_visibleLeaders`, `_isLeaderVisibleForActiveView`, `_leaderPillCount`, `_renderLeaderStrip`, `_maybeRenderLeaderHelp`, `_invalidateLeadersCache`. ''New constant'' `HINT_LEADER`. ''Files:'' cp-leaders.js (per-view filter, pill rendering, help reuse), cascade-palette-widget.js (strip el + DOM order + listeners + setFocus branch + hint dispatch + change-hook leader-invalidation), cp-keyboard.js (LEADER_KEY_DESC + dispatcher + _isPillFocus + _pillsCycle), cp-views.js (`_setActiveView` re-renders leader strip on view change), cp-constants.js (HINT_LEADER), styles.tid (purple-accent strip + pill + key-chip + focused + dark). ''Structure pills now scroll instead of truncating.'' Three layered truncations were chopping long filters in the Structure strip's per-layer rows: (1) JS-level ‚Äî `_layerPills` ran every value through a `_truncate(s, 50‚Äì80)` cap that returned `"abc‚Ä¶"` BEFORE the value ever reached the DOM, so CSS scroll could never help; (2) CSS-level ‚Äî each pill had `max-width: 100%; overflow: hidden` and the pill's value had `text-overflow: ellipsis; white-space: nowrap` so even untruncated strings got clipped at the popup edge; (3) row-level ‚Äî `flex-wrap: wrap` meant pills broke to a new line rather than scrolling. All three removed. ''JS:'' `_layerPills` passes raw filter / value strings; the `_truncate` helper is deleted (dead code). The `sort` pill's `custom: <key>` prefix is kept; the key is no longer chopped. ''CSS:'' per-layer rows are `nowrap` + `overflow-x: auto`, pills are `flex-shrink: 0` and render at their natural width, value has plain `white-space: nowrap` (no ellipsis). Keyboard nav calls `scrollIntoView({inline: "nearest"})` on the focused pill so ‚Üê/‚Üí walks past the visible edge transparently ‚Äî matches the preset / leader strip pattern. Thin scrollbar styled (light + dark). ''Bonus:'' Structure strip's focused state used a full 1px ring (`inset 0 0 0 1px`) instead of the 2px left-edge bar (`inset 2px 0 0 0`) that preset / leader / etc. all use ‚Äî aligned to the standard so all focusable strips have a consistent focus cue. ''Files:'' styles.tid, cp-views.js. JS module changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.48 |2026-05-25 |''Docs pass for the focusable Structure strip (0.0.46-47).'' Reconciles the user-facing surface with the new interaction model: ''reference.tid'' focus-model intro rewritten ‚Äî the Structure strip is now described as ''always present when the active view declares layers'' (was "informational only"), with the compact-default ‚Üí expand-on-demand ‚Üí 4-arrow grid model spelled out; ''pills group'' now lists "structure" as the fifth section, and the Tab table row updates the pill cycle order to ''preset ‚Üí visibility ‚Üí filter ‚Üí view ‚Üí structure''. ''Keyboard table'' gains six new Structure-strip rows: ‚Üµ/Space/‚Üí to expand from compact; ‚Üë/‚Üì in compact to walk to adjacent pill sections (the 0.0.47 fix); ‚Üê/‚Üí within an expanded sub-row; ‚Üë/‚Üì across sub-rows with the boundary-crossing auto-collapse + step-out into the adjacent section; Esc in expanded collapses; Esc in compact returns to input. ''readme.tid'' updates the Multi-view-root-menu bullet to describe Structure as focusable + compact/expand, and the Keyboard-first bullet adds ''structure'' to the Tab cycle order. No code changes ‚Äî pure documentation pass. |
|0.0.47 |2026-05-25 |''Structure strip: vertical pill-row navigation + auto-collapse on row crossing.'' Two fixes to the 0.0.46 focusable Structure strip. ''Bug: Up/Down in compact mode'' bubbled to the background wiki and scrolled the page behind the popup, because the compact-mode keydown handler ignored those keys. Fixed: ‚Üë walks to the previous pill section (the visual pill row above ‚Äî view / filter / etc.), ‚Üì walks to the next pill section or drops into input. Matches the existing other-pill-strip behaviour. ''New: vertical exit from expanded mode'' ‚Äî ‚Üë on the topmost pill subrow now ''collapses the strip back to compact'' and lands focus on the pill section above; ‚Üì on the bottommost pill subrow collapses + lands focus on the section below (or input if there's nothing below). Internal-row ‚Üë/‚Üì continues to move within the expanded pill grid as before. The "collapse on crossing" rule keeps the strip's interaction surface predictable ‚Äî leaving with the strip still expanded would surprise the user on next Tab-back. New helpers `_viewConfigStepOut(direction)` in cp-keyboard.js + `_viewConfigAtTopRow` / `_viewConfigAtBottomRow` in cp-views.js. ''Files:'' cp-keyboard.js (`_handleKeydownViewConfig` adds compact-mode ‚Üë/‚Üì branch + expanded-mode boundary detection), cp-views.js (row-detection helpers). JS module changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.46 |2026-05-25 |''Focusable Structure strip with compact/expand modes.'' The Structure pill row that was strictly informational since 0.0.37 now joins the Tab cycle as a new ''viewconfig'' focus section, with a two-stage interaction model: ''compact'' (initial) and ''expanded'' (on demand). Compact mode shows a single summary row ‚Äî view name, layer count + composition, and any view-scoped pills (sort / entries-mode / grouping). Pressing ''Enter / Space / ‚Üí'' from focused-compact expands to the full stacked layout (view-scoped header row + one mini-row per layer with all primitive pills); pressing ''Esc'' collapses back. ''4-arrow grid navigation'' in expanded mode: ‚Üê/‚Üí walks pills within a row, ‚Üë/‚Üì moves across rows. The currently-focused pill auto-renders contextual help into the details drawer ‚Äî pill kind, the actual filter / value, the owning layer, and a per-kind description (e.g. "Filter producing child rows under a parent. <currentTiddler> is the parent's title"). Ctrl-hold still works as the standard manual preview gate. Each focus-entry to the strip starts compact ‚Äî explicit expansion is required each visit, by design, so the strip stays unobtrusive in the Tab cycle. Click on a pill in expanded mode focuses it (mirrors mousedown on other strips). ''Pill cycle:'' viewconfig joins the pill group at the end (visual order: preset ‚Üí visibility ‚Üí filter ‚Üí view ‚Üí viewconfig ‚Üí input ‚Üí menu ‚Üí details), so Shift-Tab from input lands directly on the structure strip and ‚Üë-from-input lands there too. ''Focused styling:'' the strip background lifts to a subtle blue when focused; the focused pill picks up a saturated indigo border + filled background. Light + dark variants. ''New constants'' `HINT_VIEWCONFIG_COMPACT` and `HINT_VIEWCONFIG_EXPANDED`. ''New methods:'' `_hasViewConfigToShow`, `_renderViewConfigCompact`, `_renderViewConfigExpanded`, `_viewConfigGrid`, `_viewConfigMove`, `_maybeRenderViewConfigHelp`, `_viewConfigPillHelp`, `_handleKeydownViewConfig`. ''Files:'' cp-views.js (compact / expanded renderers + grid nav + per-pill-kind help map), cp-keyboard.js (`_pillsCycle` adds viewconfig, `_isPillFocus` extended, `_handleKeydownViewConfig` dispatcher, tier-3 switch case), cascade-palette-widget.js (tabindex, focus listener, setFocus branch + initialisation, hint dispatch, render-strip cleanup), cp-constants.js (hint constants), styles.tid (focused strip outline, focused pill highlight, light + dark). JS module changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.45 |2026-05-25 |''Docs + cleanup pass.'' Consolidates the 0.0.40-44 changes (Space opens action menu on typed rows, Esc walks one stage back from input AND menu, Shift-Esc closes from any depth/focus) into the user-facing surface and tightens code around them. ''Docs:'' `doc/reference.tid` (focus model intro rewritten, keyboard table row for Esc/input updated to "Pop one stage; close at root", new Shift-Esc row, Esc/menu row separated from the other-section Esc row, Space-on-typed-row row added under menu gestures, entity-type drill section now shows two reach paths ‚Äî Right-arrow leaf-only OR Space leaf-or-container ‚Äî and notes the per-row preview badge applies to containers too), `doc/architecture.tid` (stage-stack stanza now lists tree + confirm kinds, keyboard router lines updated for Right-arrow/Space/Esc/Shift-Esc semantics), `doc/overview.tid` + `readme.tid` (key-narrative sentences updated to reflect "‚Üí Space Esc Enter" and the Esc-back / Shift-Esc-close distinction), `doc/protocol.tid` (Projects-with-Tasks example clarifies container vs leaf reach via Space vs Right-arrow), `doc/examples.tid` (stale "Tab" references for action-menu drill corrected to Right-arrow). ''Code cleanup:'' (a) ''Shift-Esc now ordered before pick-mode Esc cancel'' ‚Äî previously a Shift-Esc during pick-mode cancelled pick-mode rather than closing, contradicting the documented "always closes" intent. The two `Esc` global handlers in `_handleKeydown` swap order so the modifier-keyed close wins outright. (b) ''Dead ternary removed'' ‚Äî `fireSelected`'s drill branch had `parentPicked = stage.kind === "actions" ? (stage.parentPicked || null) : (stage.parentPicked || null)` (both arms identical). Collapsed to a single expression. (c) ''Stale comment'' "Tab on a leaf is a no-op" updated to describe the actual current behaviour (Right-arrow on a non-typed, non-drill leaf is the no-op; Enter fires the action). ''Files:'' doc/reference.tid, doc/architecture.tid, doc/overview.tid, d