|0.0.44 |2026-05-25 |''Shift-Esc closes the palette from any focus and any depth.'' Companion to the 0.0.41-43 Esc-pops-stage redesign. Bare Esc now walks the breadcrumb back one stage at a time; Shift-Esc is the ''I'm done'' shortcut that collapses the whole stack in one keystroke regardless of where focus is (input / menu / pill strips). Implemented as a Tier 2 global handler in `_handleKeydown` so it precedes section-specific Esc handlers. Pick-mode Esc cancellation still wins for bare Esc; Shift-Esc bypasses pick-mode cleanup and just closes. `HINT_INPUT` updated to ''Esc back ¬∑ Shift-Esc close''. ''Files:'' cp-keyboard.js (`_handleKeydown` global Shift-Esc branch), cp-constants.js (`HINT_INPUT`). JS module changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.43 |2026-05-25 |''Esc-in-menu pops one stage universally (not just inside action subtrees).'' Generalises the 0.0.42 change: at any depth > 1, Esc-in-menu pops one stage and keeps menu focus on the prior stage ‚Äî for tree / filter / action / confirm alike. At root depth (nothing to pop), Esc still refocuses input so the user can type to filter root results. Result: Esc-in-input and Esc-in-menu are now both ''one keystroke = one step back, keeping current focus context'', symmetric with ArrowLeft-in-menu. The user walks the breadcrumb right-to-left keystroke-by-keystroke from anywhere ‚Äî no detour through input mid-walk. ''Files:'' cp-keyboard.js (`_handleKeydownMenu` Esc branch). JS module changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.42 |2026-05-25 |''Esc-in-menu pops one stage directly inside an action subtree.'' Inside an action-menu stage (or a confirm pushed from one), Esc-while-focused-on-menu now pops one stage and ''keeps'' menu focus on the prior stage ‚Äî rather than first jumping to input (which was the legacy behaviour for all menu Esc). So backing out of a wrongly-drilled action is one keystroke that lands the user on the previous menu, ready to pick again, instead of two (Esc ‚Üí input, Esc ‚Üí pop). Scope: only `stage.kind === "actions"` or `"confirm"` get the new behaviour; tree / filter / root menus keep Esc ‚Üí input so typing to filter the current level remains a single keystroke. ArrowLeft-in-menu still pops at any depth ‚Äî it was already symmetric. ''Files:'' cp-keyboard.js (`_handleKeydownMenu` Esc branch). JS module changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.41 |2026-05-25 |''Esc in input pops one stage instead of always closing.'' Previously Esc-in-input closed the palette regardless of stack depth ‚Äî meaning a deep action-subtree (entity drill ‚Üí action menu ‚Üí confirm) was a single-keystroke jump back to nothing. New rule: ''Esc backs out one stage at any depth > 1; only closes at root.'' Symmetric with ArrowLeft-in-menu (which already pops). Now ''Esc'' applied repeatedly walks the breadcrumb from right to left, finally closing at root ‚Äî so a wrong drill into an action menu is recoverable without rebuilding context, and an N-deep stack closes in N keystrokes. Esc-in-menu is unchanged (still refocuses input) since that's a focus gesture, not a stack gesture; users have ArrowLeft for stage-pop in menu focus. Pick-mode Esc cancellation (Tier 2a' global handler) still wins ‚Äî bailing out of a sub-pick still returns to the pre-pick view from any focus. `HINT_INPUT` updated to ''Esc back/close''. ''Files:'' cp-keyboard.js (`_handleKeydownInput`), cp-constants.js (`HINT_INPUT`). JS module changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.40 |2026-05-25 |''Space-to-trigger-actions on typed rows + bugfix: ca-confirm picked binding in action-menu stages.'' Two coupled changes. ''Bug:'' an action declared with `ca-confirm: yes` and `ca-actions: <$action-deletetiddler $tiddler=<<picked>>/>` (the shipped tag-tree-node delete action being the trigger) did nothing on Confirm. Root cause: the confirm-wrap branch in `fireSelected` always built its `vars` with `picked = picked.title`, but in an action-menu stage `picked` is the chosen ''action'' tiddler ‚Äî not the entity being acted upon. So `<<picked>>` resolved to the action's own title (a shadow tiddler that can't be deleted) and the operation silently no-op'd. Fix matches `fireLeafAction`'s logic: when `stage.kind === "actions"`, bind the vars' picked to `stage.parentPicked` (the entity). Direct-fire and confirm-wrapped paths are now symmetric ‚Äî a `ca-actions` referencing `<<picked>>` resolves to the same entity regardless of whether the action has a confirm gate. ''Space-to-open-actions.'' Pressing ''Space'' on a row with a non-empty `entityType` now pushes the action-menu stage of that type ‚Äî mirroring Right-arrow's existing leaf-only behaviour AND additionally enabling action invocation on ''containers'' (where Right-arrow still descends into children). Resolves the "how do I reach the action menu on a tag-tree folder?" gap. Existing Space bindings (toggle flip, text/number/date edit) keep precedence on rows of those kinds ‚Äî entity-type firing is checked after the kind-specific handlers. The per-row `‚ÜíN` action-preview badge no longer restricts to leaves either ‚Äî containers with applicable actions get the badge too, with the tooltip indicating "Space" as the trigger (vs. "Space or Right-arrow" on leaves). `HINT_MENU` updated to read ''Space actions/toggle/edit'' so the new binding is discoverable in the footer. The 0.0.38 doc-note "containers don't expose the action menu ‚Äî planned follow-up via a synthetic `[Actions]` first-child row" is obsolete and removed; Space replaces that planned mechanism with a simpler keystroke. ''Files:'' cp-firing.js (confirm-wrap vars), cp-keyboard.js (Space ‚Üí action menu), cp-rendering.js (preview badge gate + tooltip), cp-constants.js (HINT_MENU), doc/reference.tid. JS module changed ‚Äî restart required. |
|0.0.39 |2026-05-24 |''Filter-based action applicability + per-row action preview + perf footer.'' Three threads that extend the entity-type drill mechanism shipped in 0.0.38 with per-instance applicability, externalise WHICH actions a row would expose on drill, and give the user a diagnostic surface to verify the cost. ''Filter-based applicability (`ca-action-when`).'' An action tiddler may declare an optional ''`ca-action-when`'' filter, evaluated with `<currentTiddler>` bound to the picked entity. Non-empty result ‚áí applicable; empty / missing filter ‚áí always applicable (back-compat with all pre-0.0.39 actions). The applicability filter narrows both the action-menu population (`loadActionsForType` now takes a context tiddler) and the per-row preview count. Typical patterns: `[<currentTiddler>!has[done]]` for "Mark done"; `[<currentTiddler>!is[system]]` for "Delete"; `[<currentTiddler>tags[]match[project]]` for domain-specific actions. The default-action lookup (`lookupEntityDefaultActions`, used by 3-tier Enter fallback in `ca-next-scope` stages) is intentionally NOT gated ‚Äî author-marked `ca-default: yes` is the gate there. ''Per-row action preview.'' Tree-view rows that carry a resolved entity type now render a small `‚ÜíN` badge showing how many actions would appear on Right-arrow drill. The count is computed by running the action loader (entity-type match + `ca-action-when` evaluation) against each visible row. Memoised by `(entityType, title)` within a render pass ‚Äî keystroke-driven recomputations that just narrow the visible list hit the cache. Per-view opt-out via ''`ca-view-show-action-preview: no`'' (default yes). The cache is reset at the top of every `renderResults` call so wiki changes and stage push/pop invalidate it cleanly. CSS adds `.rcp-row-action-preview` (light + dark + menu-focused-selected variants). ''Perf footer (configurable).'' New config tiddler ''`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/show-perf-footer`'' (default `no`) toggles a small